{"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"JbvDRIyoAI2S"},"source":["# Project Framework: Wearable-Based Calorie Estimation App"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"A1toiVg8AL8I"},"source":["## Vision\n","A web application that gives users personalized calorie estimates and activity recommendations using real wearable sensor data from two different populations. The app adjusts results based on the user’s age group, reflects actual activity intensity measured by sensors, and can also consider weather conditions. Behind it is a data pipeline that turns raw accelerometer recordings into a ready to use analytical database that does not depend on body weight."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"td6if0aZT_IQ"},"source":["# Section 4.1: Data Acquisition & Ingestion\n","\n","Raw data is pulled from each source: UCI CSVs downloaded manually, weather fetched from the Open-Meteo API, and MET values scraped from the Compendium website. Each source lands in local storage in its native format.\n","\n","This section pulls the three raw data sources (HARTH CSVs, HAR70+ CSVs, Open-Meteo JSON,\n","and MET Compendium HTML) from their origins and stores them locally as raw\n","artifacts, ready for the cleaning stage.\n","\n","## Relationship to downstream notebooks\n","This notebook produces the raw inputs consumed by `02_cleaning_transformation.ipynb`.\n","Nothing in this notebook modifies, standardizes, or cleans the data, it only\n","fetches and persists.\n","\n","## Outputs\n","- `Data/harth/` : 22 subject CSVs (manual download from UCI, verified here)\n","- `Data/har70plus/` : 18 subject CSVs (manual download from UCI, verified here)  \n","- `Data/weather_raw.json` : Open-Meteo API response for the HARTH + HAR70+ date range\n","- `Data/met_lookup.csv` : MET reference table scraped from the Compendium"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":1,"metadata":{"id":"bxKBcwOyUJgl","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070076039,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":503,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}}},"outputs":[],"source":["# Importing necessary libraries\n","\n","# Standard library\n","import json                         # parse and save Open-Meteo JSON response\n","import time                         # backoff for API retries\n","from pathlib import Path            # clean, OS-independent file path handling\n","import warnings                     # suppress expected pandas warnings\n","import sqlite3                      # SQLite database driver\n","\n","# Data handling\n","import numpy as np                  # numerical operations\n","import pandas as pd                 # save MET table as CSV\n","import requests                     # fetch data from Open-Meteo API and MET website\n","\n","# Web scraping\n","from bs4 import BeautifulSoup       # parse MET Compendium HTML table\n","\n","# Visualization\n","import matplotlib.pyplot as plt     # plots for data quality evidence"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":2,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"executionInfo":{"elapsed":22373,"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070098439,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"},"user_tz":-180},"id":"vvxqPkbTUOdf","outputId":"e89b458a-05fb-4a72-a0e7-2e521f21c60a"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Mounted at /content/drive\n","Data directory: /content/drive/MyDrive/Data Processing Project/Data\n","HARTH folder:   /content/drive/MyDrive/Data Processing Project/Data/harth\n","HAR70+ folder:  /content/drive/MyDrive/Data Processing Project/Data/har70plus\n","Weather output: /content/drive/MyDrive/Data Processing Project/Data/weather_raw.json\n","MET output:     /content/drive/MyDrive/Data Processing Project/Data/met_lookup.csv\n"]}],"source":["# Resolve DATA_PATH: Colab if available, otherwise local VS Code layout\n","try:\n","    # Running in Google Colab → mount Google Drive and write data there\n","    from google.colab import drive\n","    drive.mount(\"/content/drive\")\n","    DATA_PATH = Path(\"/content/drive/MyDrive/Data Processing Project/Data\")\n","except (ImportError, ModuleNotFoundError):\n","    # Running locally → notebook lives in PROJECT/Notebooks/, data lives in PROJECT/Data/\n","    DATA_PATH = (Path.cwd() / \"..\" / \"Data\").resolve()\n","\n","# Expected sub-folders and output paths\n","HARTH_PATH  = DATA_PATH / \"harth\"\n","HAR70_PATH  = DATA_PATH / \"har70plus\"\n","WEATHER_RAW = DATA_PATH / \"weather_raw.json\"\n","MET_OUT     = DATA_PATH / \"met_lookup.csv\"\n","\n","# Ensure the Data directory exists (creates it if running for the first time)\n","DATA_PATH.mkdir(exist_ok=True)\n","\n","print(f\"Data directory: {DATA_PATH}\")\n","print(f\"HARTH folder:   {HARTH_PATH}\")\n","print(f\"HAR70+ folder:  {HAR70_PATH}\")\n","print(f\"Weather output: {WEATHER_RAW}\")\n","print(f\"MET output:     {MET_OUT}\")"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"2Z6NmbhXUaps"},"source":["\n","\n","This cell resolves file paths dynamically so the notebook works on any of our machines. Output paths are defined upfront so the rest of the notebook is a clean sequence of \"fetch X, save to path Y.\""]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"93H-YrWcUwAX"},"source":["### HARTH and HAR70+"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":3,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"executionInfo":{"elapsed":1775,"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070100216,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"},"user_tz":-180},"id":"3jPLX2rSUiiG","outputId":"072a9244-f4ff-4f21-a32a-114daac8170d"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Verifying HARTH download...\n","  HARTH: 22 files, 855.0 MB total\n","    first file: S006.csv\n","    last file:  S029.csv\n","\n","Verifying HAR70+ download...\n","  HAR70+: 18 files, 205.1 MB total\n","    first file: 501.csv\n","    last file:  518.csv\n"]}],"source":["## A. HARTH and HAR70+: manual download verification\n","\n","# Both datasets are downloaded manually from the UCI Machine Learning Repository as ZIP archives, then extracted into Data/harth/ and Data/har70plus/.\n","\n","# Manual download is the right choice here: these are static research datasets that don't update, UCI doesn't offer a stable API, and the ZIPs are 10-50 MB each, a one-time download is simpler than scripting it.\n","\n","# This cell verifies that the expected files exist and logs basic facts about them.\n","\n","def verify_csv_folder(folder: Path, source_name: str, expected_files: int) -> None:\n","    \"\"\"Check that a folder exists, contains CSVs, and matches the expected count.\"\"\"\n","    assert folder.exists(), f\"{source_name} folder not found: {folder}\\n\" \\\n","        f\"Please download from UCI and extract into {folder}\"\n","\n","    csv_files = sorted(folder.glob(\"*.csv\"))\n","\n","    assert len(csv_files) == expected_files, \\\n","        f\"{source_name}: expected {expected_files} CSV files, found {len(csv_files)}\"\n","\n","    # Compute total disk size so we know how much raw data we're working with\n","    total_size_mb = sum(f.stat().st_size for f in csv_files) / 1e6\n","\n","    print(f\"  {source_name}: {len(csv_files)} files, {total_size_mb:.1f} MB total\")\n","    print(f\"    first file: {csv_files[0].name}\")\n","    print(f\"    last file:  {csv_files[-1].name}\")\n","\n","print(\"Verifying HARTH download...\")\n","verify_csv_folder(HARTH_PATH, \"HARTH\", expected_files=22)\n","\n","print(\"\\nVerifying HAR70+ download...\")\n","verify_csv_folder(HAR70_PATH, \"HAR70+\", expected_files=18)"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"S88UU5hsUlk5"},"source":["This cell verifies that the HARTH and HAR70+ downloads are complete: 22 files for HARTH, 18 files for HAR70+, before the pipeline continues. Fail-loud assertions prevent the next steps in this notebook from running on incomplete data. No data modification happens here so the raw CSVs stay exactly as downloaded from UCI."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"VydDDoiUUz6H"},"source":["### Open-Meteo"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"GDOZzCgbgG59"},"source":["Hourly Trondheim weather is not fetched in this notebook. It is prepared in the separate `weather_preparation.ipynb`, which handles the API request, investigates HARTH timestamp anonymization, and builds climate profiles for the 21 HARTH subjects whose dates were replaced (1 subject only had the date leaked - according to data collectors).\n","\n","The output file, `weather_raw.json`, contains the Open Meteo weather data along with a project_metadata section that stores the timestamp findings and two climate profiles: `s1_bulk` for Session 1 (Oct to Nov 2016) and `s2_bulk` for Session 2 (Oct to Nov 2017 to 2021).\n","The cell below simply checks that the file exists."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":4,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"executionInfo":{"elapsed":1482,"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070101700,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"},"user_tz":-180},"id":"lP9YbSnmUt4a","outputId":"a04c423d-98c3-4592-901b-307486a2abe0"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["✓ weather_raw.json verified\n","  File:              /content/drive/MyDrive/Data Processing Project/Data/weather_raw.json\n","  Size:              9.2 MB\n","  Hourly records:    192,888\n","  Climatology pools: 2\n","  Fetched at:        2026-04-23T13:05:20+00:00\n"]}],"source":["## B. Open-Meteo historical weather verification\n","\n","# The weather_raw.json file is produced by the standalone notebook\n","# `weather_preparation.ipynb`, which handles the Open-Meteo API fetch,\n","# the forensic analysis of HARTH's date anonymization, and the\n","# construction of stratified climatology profiles. That notebook must\n","# be run before this one.\n","#\n","# This cell just verifies the file is present and has the rich structure\n","# this notebook expects (hourly block + project_metadata).\n","\n","assert WEATHER_RAW.exists(), (\n","    f\"weather_raw.json not found at {WEATHER_RAW}. \"\n","    f\"Run the standalone `weather_preparation.ipynb` first — it fetches \"\n","    f\"the Open-Meteo corpus and embeds the forensic climatology metadata.\"\n",")\n","\n","with open(WEATHER_RAW) as fh:\n","    _probe = json.load(fh)\n","\n","# Shape checks\n","assert \"hourly\" in _probe, \"weather_raw.json missing 'hourly' block\"\n","assert \"project_metadata\" in _probe, (\n","    \"weather_raw.json predates the forensic-aware pipeline — \"\n","    \"re-run weather_preparation.ipynb to regenerate.\"\n",")\n","assert \"climatology_profiles\" in _probe[\"project_metadata\"], \\\n","    \"project_metadata missing climatology_profiles\"\n","\n","n_hours = len(_probe[\"hourly\"][\"time\"])\n","n_profiles = len(_probe[\"project_metadata\"][\"climatology_profiles\"])\n","fetched_at = _probe[\"project_metadata\"].get(\"fetched_at\", \"unknown\")\n","file_size_mb = WEATHER_RAW.stat().st_size / 1e6\n","\n","print(f\"✓ weather_raw.json verified\")\n","print(f\"  File:              {WEATHER_RAW}\")\n","print(f\"  Size:              {file_size_mb:.1f} MB\")\n","print(f\"  Hourly records:    {n_hours:,}\")\n","print(f\"  Climatology pools: {n_profiles}\")\n","print(f\"  Fetched at:        {fetched_at}\")\n","\n","del _probe"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"FFiQDQr4U_LN"},"source":["This cell verifies that `weather_raw.json` has been produced by the\n","weather preparation notebook and has the expected rich structure.\n","The main cleaning work happens in section F below, where the JSON is\n","parsed into a tabular weather frame and the climatology profiles are\n","lifted into a ready-to-use DataFrame."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"w2_hmJ4aWNT_"},"source":["### MET Compendium"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":5,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"executionInfo":{"elapsed":966,"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070102668,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"},"user_tz":-180},"id":"fWr2WVh8Vq8Q","outputId":"242eeb7f-050d-4b15-f92d-73d748f47cae"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Scraping pacompendium.com...\n","  ✓ heading 01: 44 codes from https://pacompendium.com/bicycling/\n","  ✓ heading 07: 17 codes from https://pacompendium.com/inactivity/\n","  ✓ heading 12: 66 codes from https://pacompendium.com/running/\n","  ✓ heading 17: 93 codes from https://pacompendium.com/walking/\n","\n","Created MET lookup: 12 activities\n","  Scraped live:       12\n","  Hardcoded fallback: 0\n","  Proxy mappings:     3\n","  Saved to:           /content/drive/MyDrive/Data Processing Project/Data/met_lookup.csv\n","\n","✓ All 12 scraped values match hardcoded constants exactly.\n","\n","Proxy mappings (activity → closest Compendium entry):\n","  • shuffling                 → 17151  \"Walking, less than 2.0 mph, level, strolling, very slow\"\n","  • cycling_sit_inactive      → 07021  \"Sitting quietly (bike coasting, rider seated)\"\n","  • cycling_stand_inactive    → 07040  \"Standing quietly (bike coasting, rider standing)\"\n","\n","              activity  met_value compendium_code  is_proxy  source\n","               sitting        1.0           07021     False scraped\n","                 lying        1.0           07011     False scraped\n","              standing        1.3           07040     False scraped\n","             shuffling        2.3           17151      True scraped\n","               walking        4.0           17255     False scraped\n","             stairs_up        4.5           17133     False scraped\n","           stairs_down        3.5           17070     False scraped\n","               running        9.3           12050     False scraped\n","           cycling_sit        6.8           01020     False scraped\n","         cycling_stand        7.0           01016     False scraped\n","  cycling_sit_inactive        1.0           07021      True scraped\n","cycling_stand_inactive        1.3           07040      True scraped\n"]}],"source":["## C. MET Compendium — scrape-first with hardcoded fallback\n","\n","# The 2024 Adult Compendium publishes MET values at pacompendium.com, grouped\n","# by Major Heading (the first two digits of each 5-digit code). We attempt to\n","# scrape the relevant category pages; every row also has a hardcoded fallback\n","# curated from the 2024 Compendium PDF (Ainsworth et al.), so the pipeline\n","# runs end-to-end even when the site is unreachable.\n","#\n","# Each row records its value provenance in `source` ('scraped' or\n","# 'hardcoded_fallback') and its mapping provenance in `is_proxy` (True when\n","# the activity has no direct Compendium match and uses the closest\n","# semantically equivalent code).\n","\n","from io import StringIO\n","\n","HEADERS = {'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (AUB MSBA 305 academic project)'}\n","\n","#  Hardcoded values + closest-activity proxy mappings\n","# For each activity: (met_value, 5-digit_code, is_proxy, compendium_description).\n","# Proxy rows document explicitly WHICH Compendium code we map to and why.\n","MET_HARDCODED = {\n","    'sitting':                (1.0, '07021', False, 'Sitting quietly, general'),\n","    'lying':                  (1.0, '07011', False, 'Lying quietly, doing nothing'),\n","    'standing':               (1.3, '07040', False, 'Standing quietly'),\n","    'shuffling':              (2.3, '17151', True,  'Walking, less than 2.0 mph, level, strolling, very slow'),\n","    'walking':                (4.0, '17255', False, 'Walking, self-selected speed, indoor track or outdoors, firm surface'),\n","    'stairs_up':              (4.5, '17133', False, 'Stair climbing, slow pace'),\n","    'stairs_down':            (3.5, '17070', False, 'Descending stairs'),\n","    'running':                (9.3, '12050', False, 'Running, 6 to 6.3 mph (10 min/mile)'),\n","    'cycling_sit':            (6.8, '01020', False, 'Bicycling 10-11.9 mph, leisure'),\n","    'cycling_stand':          (7.0, '01016', False, 'Bicycling, self-selected moderate pace'),\n","    'cycling_sit_inactive':   (1.0, '07021', True,  'Sitting quietly (bike coasting, rider seated)'),\n","    'cycling_stand_inactive': (1.3, '07040', True,  'Standing quietly (bike coasting, rider standing)'),\n","}\n","\n","#  Category URLs\n","# Prefix → URL candidates. First match wins. Simple slugs on pacompendium.com.\n","CATEGORY_URLS = {\n","    '01': ['https://pacompendium.com/bicycling/'],\n","    '07': ['https://pacompendium.com/inactivity/'],\n","    '12': ['https://pacompendium.com/running/'],\n","    '17': ['https://pacompendium.com/walking/'],\n","}\n","\n","\n","def _extract_code_met_pairs(df):\n","    \"\"\"Scan a DataFrame row by row. A Compendium entry is any row that\n","    contains both a 5-digit integer code and a float in the MET range\n","    (0.5 to 25). Ignores column names entirely — works even when the table\n","    has no detectable header row.\"\"\"\n","    found = {}\n","    for _, row in df.iterrows():\n","        values = [str(v).strip() for v in row.values]\n","        code = met = None\n","        for v in values:\n","            if code is None and v.isdigit() and len(v) == 5:\n","                code = v\n","                continue\n","            if met is None:\n","                try:\n","                    f = float(v)\n","                    # 5-digit codes look like floats too (17070.0) — exclude them\n","                    if 0.5 <= f <= 25 and not (v.replace('.', '').isdigit() and len(v.split('.')[0]) == 5):\n","                        met = f\n","                except ValueError:\n","                    continue\n","        if code is not None and met is not None:\n","            found[code] = met\n","    return found\n","\n","\n","def scrape_category(candidate_urls, timeout=15):\n","    \"\"\"Try each URL; return ({code: met}, used_url) from first success.\"\"\"\n","    for url in candidate_urls:\n","        try:\n","            resp = requests.get(url, headers=HEADERS, timeout=timeout)\n","            resp.raise_for_status()\n","            tables = pd.read_html(StringIO(resp.text))\n","            codes = {}\n","            for tbl in tables:\n","                codes.update(_extract_code_met_pairs(tbl))\n","            if codes:\n","                return codes, url\n","            print(f\"  — {url}: {len(tables)} table(s) parsed but no code/MET pairs found\")\n","        except (requests.RequestException, ValueError) as e:\n","            print(f\"  ! {url} — {type(e).__name__}: {e}\")\n","    return {}, None\n","\n","\n","# Run the scrape\n","print(\"Scraping pacompendium.com...\")\n","scraped_codes = {}\n","for prefix, urls in CATEGORY_URLS.items():\n","    page_data, used_url = scrape_category(urls)\n","    if page_data:\n","        scraped_codes.update(page_data)\n","        print(f\"  ✓ heading {prefix}: {len(page_data)} codes from {used_url}\")\n","    else:\n","        print(f\"  ✗ heading {prefix}: all URL candidates failed — fallback in use\")\n","\n","# Build lookup, row by row, record provenance + drift\n","rows = []\n","n_scraped = n_fallback = 0\n","drift = []\n","\n","for activity, (hc_met, code, is_proxy, description) in MET_HARDCODED.items():\n","    if code in scraped_codes:\n","        met_value = scraped_codes[code]\n","        source    = 'scraped'\n","        n_scraped += 1\n","        if abs(met_value - hc_met) > 0.01:\n","            drift.append((activity, code, hc_met, met_value))\n","    else:\n","        met_value = hc_met\n","        source    = 'hardcoded_fallback'\n","        n_fallback += 1\n","    rows.append({\n","        'activity':        activity,\n","        'met_value':       met_value,\n","        'compendium_code': code,\n","        'is_proxy':        is_proxy,\n","        'source':          source,\n","    })\n","\n","met_lookup = pd.DataFrame(rows)\n","met_lookup.to_csv(DATA_PATH / 'met_lookup.csv', index=False)\n","\n","# Report\n","print(f\"\\nCreated MET lookup: {len(met_lookup)} activities\")\n","print(f\"  Scraped live:       {n_scraped}\")\n","print(f\"  Hardcoded fallback: {n_fallback}\")\n","print(f\"  Proxy mappings:     {int(met_lookup['is_proxy'].sum())}\")\n","print(f\"  Saved to:           {DATA_PATH / 'met_lookup.csv'}\")\n","\n","# Drift report: tells us if any hardcoded value disagrees with the live site\n","if drift:\n","    print(\"\\n⚠ Drift — scraped values differ from hardcoded constants:\")\n","    for act, code, hc, sc in drift:\n","        print(f\"  • {act:25s} code {code}  hardcoded={hc}  scraped={sc}\")\n","    print(\"  Action: check if the Compendium was updated; adjust MET_HARDCODED if so.\")\n","else:\n","    if n_scraped > 0:\n","        print(f\"\\n✓ All {n_scraped} scraped values match hardcoded constants exactly.\")\n","\n","# Proxy documentation: show which Compendium activity each proxy maps to\n","proxy_rows = [(act, *MET_HARDCODED[act][1:]) for act in MET_HARDCODED\n","              if MET_HARDCODED[act][2]]\n","if proxy_rows:\n","    print(\"\\nProxy mappings (activity → closest Compendium entry):\")\n","    for act, code, _, desc in proxy_rows:\n","        print(f\"  • {act:25s} → {code}  \\\"{desc}\\\"\")\n","\n","print(\"\\n\" + met_lookup.to_string(index=False))"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"A5XVaSUFVvIt"},"source":["This cell builds the MET lookup table using a \"trust but verify\" approach.\n","\n","Values are hardcoded from the 2024 Compendium of Physical Activities PDF (Ainsworth et al.) as a reliable baseline.\n","\n","Simultaneously, the code attempts to scrape the live Compendium website and compares scraped values against the hardcoded baseline. This comparison produces three important pieces of information:\n","\n","- Provenance: Every row records where its value came from 'scraped' or 'hardcoded_fallback' so anyone reviewing the pipeline knows whether a given MET value was pulled from the live site or the curated PDF.\n","- Proxy flagging: Three activities in our datasets (shuffling, cycling_sit_inactive, cycling_stand_inactive) have no direct Compendium entry and are mapped to the closest semantically equivalent code. The is_proxy flag makes these judgment calls explicit in the data rather than hidden in the code.\n","- Drift detection: If a scraped value disagrees with the hardcoded constant by more than 0.01 MET, the notebook prints a drift report. This is an early-warning system: if the Compendium is updated in a future edition, we notice immediately rather than silently using stale hardcoded values.\n","\n","On this run, all scraped values matched their hardcoded counterparts exactly, confirming our baseline is current.\n","The output is a small lookup table with five columns (activity, met_value, compendium_code, is_proxy, source) written to met_lookup.csv.\n","Our next steps read from this file; they never re-scrape or re-derive MET values."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"M_6CtZxgWRHy"},"source":["### Summary"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":6,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"executionInfo":{"elapsed":11,"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070102681,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"},"user_tz":-180},"id":"3tZ50LUeWTXy","outputId":"7803acd8-be2e-4455-8095-bcb2a5647548"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Ingestion summary\n","\n","Activity CSVs:\n","  HARTH:   22 files in /content/drive/MyDrive/Data Processing Project/Data/harth\n","  HAR70+:  18 files in /content/drive/MyDrive/Data Processing Project/Data/har70plus\n","\n","Weather JSON:\n","  /content/drive/MyDrive/Data Processing Project/Data/weather_raw.json  (9.2 MB)\n","\n","MET lookup:\n","  /content/drive/MyDrive/Data Processing Project/Data/met_lookup.csv  (12 rows)\n","\n","✓ All four sources ingested. Ready for Cleaning and transformation.\n"]}],"source":["## D. Ingestion summary\n","\n","# Final verification that all four sources are now present locally and ready for the cleaning section\n","\n","print(\"Ingestion summary\\n\")\n","\n","print(\"Activity CSVs:\")\n","print(f\"  HARTH:   {len(list(HARTH_PATH.glob('*.csv')))} files in {HARTH_PATH}\")\n","print(f\"  HAR70+:  {len(list(HAR70_PATH.glob('*.csv')))} files in {HAR70_PATH}\")\n","\n","print(\"\\nWeather JSON:\")\n","weather_size_mb = WEATHER_RAW.stat().st_size / 1e6\n","print(f\"  {WEATHER_RAW}  ({weather_size_mb:.1f} MB)\")\n","\n","print(\"\\nMET lookup:\")\n","met_rows = len(pd.read_csv(MET_OUT))\n","print(f\"  {MET_OUT}  ({met_rows} rows)\")\n","\n","print(\"\\n✓ All four sources ingested. Ready for Cleaning and transformation.\")"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"Lf_PupEoWdIk"},"source":["The final cell confirms that all four data sources are now available locally as raw artifacts. This part ends where the cleaning begins: the ZIPs are extracted, the weather JSON is saved, and the MET lookup is built. Nothing has been modified or standardized yet: this comes next."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"O5RpENTzb_zq"},"source":["# Section 4.3: Data Cleaning & Transformation\n","\n","All four sources pass through a unified cleaning notebook. Schemas are reconciled, sampling rates normalized to 50Hz, timestamps parsed, dtypes enforced, duplicates checked, and quality flags (clipped samples, temporal gaps) added. Validation rules enforce data integrity before anything is saved. Outputs are cleaned CSVs stored in a dedicated folder.\n","\n","This section takes the raw sources produced by the previous part (HARTH CSVs, HAR70+\n","CSVs, Open-Meteo JSON, MET lookup CSV) and produces validated, standardized\n","outputs that downstream parts consume.\n","\n","## Relationship to other notebooks\n","- **Reads from:** `Data/harth/`, `Data/har70plus/`, `Data/weather_raw.json`, `Data/met_lookup.csv`\n","- **Writes to:** `Data/cleaned/`\n","- **Consumed by:** all future stages\n","\n","Nothing in this notebook fetches data from the network: all inputs come from\n","the local file system, produced in the ingestion.\n","\n","## Outputs\n","- `harth_cleaned.csv`: HARTH standardized at 50Hz with quality flags\n","- `har70_cleaned.csv`: HAR70+ standardized at 50Hz with quality flags\n","- `combined_cleaned.csv`: both cohorts stacked, convenience file for cross-cohort work\n","- `weather_cleaned.csv`: parsed weather with validated ranges\n","- `data_quality_report.json`: before/after statistics + decision log"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":7,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"executionInfo":{"elapsed":24,"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070102706,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"},"user_tz":-180},"id":"5o0nRyPWeAyY","outputId":"4288d277-f67d-4e0f-c61a-03c92319acde"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Inputs:\n","  HARTH:   /content/drive/MyDrive/Data Processing Project/Data/harth\n","  HAR70+:  /content/drive/MyDrive/Data Processing Project/Data/har70plus\n","  Weather: /content/drive/MyDrive/Data Processing Project/Data/weather_raw.json\n","  MET:     /content/drive/MyDrive/Data Processing Project/Data/met_lookup.csv\n","\n","Outputs → /content/drive/MyDrive/Data Processing Project/Data/cleaned\n","\n","MET lookup: 12 activities loaded\n"]}],"source":["# Input paths (produced by the ingestion notebook)\n","HARTH_PATH  = DATA_PATH / \"harth\"\n","HAR70_PATH  = DATA_PATH / \"har70plus\"\n","WEATHER_RAW = DATA_PATH / \"weather_raw.json\"\n","MET_LOOKUP  = DATA_PATH / \"met_lookup.csv\"\n","\n","# Output directory\n","CLEAN_DIR = DATA_PATH / \"cleaned\"\n","CLEAN_DIR.mkdir(exist_ok=True)\n","\n","# Sanity checks: fail fast with clear messages if any input is missing\n","assert DATA_PATH.exists(),   f\"DATA_PATH not found: {DATA_PATH}\"\n","assert HARTH_PATH.exists(),  f\"HARTH folder not found: {HARTH_PATH}\"\n","assert HAR70_PATH.exists(),  f\"HAR70+ folder not found: {HAR70_PATH}\"\n","assert WEATHER_RAW.exists(), f\"weather_raw.json not found — run 00_ingestion first\"\n","assert MET_LOOKUP.exists(),  f\"met_lookup.csv not found — run 00_ingestion first\"\n","\n","print(\"Inputs:\")\n","print(f\"  HARTH:   {HARTH_PATH}\")\n","print(f\"  HAR70+:  {HAR70_PATH}\")\n","print(f\"  Weather: {WEATHER_RAW}\")\n","print(f\"  MET:     {MET_LOOKUP}\")\n","print(f\"\\nOutputs → {CLEAN_DIR}\")\n","\n","# Load the MET lookup once: used later in activity label standardization\n","met_lookup_df = pd.read_csv(MET_LOOKUP)\n","LABEL_MAP = dict(zip(met_lookup_df[\"activity\"], met_lookup_df[\"met_value\"]))\n","ACTIVITY_NAMES = set(met_lookup_df[\"activity\"])\n","\n","print(f\"\\nMET lookup: {len(ACTIVITY_NAMES)} activities loaded\")"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"wPrKmzZweKAP"},"source":["Resolves paths for both Colab and local environments, verifies all inputs exist before proceeding, and loads the MET lookup table (built in the ingestion notebook) into memory. Any missing input halts the notebook immediately with a clear message."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":8,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"oeAbUrzveMEi","outputId":"66b10710-1a66-49bf-9b6e-cfac07f244bf","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070201410,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":98702,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Snapshotting raw HARTH...\n","Snapshotting raw HAR70+...\n","Snapshotting raw Weather JSON...\n","\n","--- BEFORE: HARTH ---\n","  source: HARTH\n","  n_files: 22\n","  n_rows: 6461328\n","  n_nulls: 0\n","  n_duplicates: 0\n","  distinct_column_signatures: 3\n","  label_dtypes_observed: ['int64']\n","  subject_id_dtype_implied_by_filename: ['str']\n","  sampling_rates_hz_observed: [50, 100]\n","\n","--- BEFORE: HAR70+ ---\n","  source: HAR70+\n","  n_files: 18\n","  n_rows: 2259597\n","  n_nulls: 0\n","  n_duplicates: 0\n","  distinct_column_signatures: 1\n","  label_dtypes_observed: ['int64']\n","  subject_id_dtype_implied_by_filename: ['int']\n","  sampling_rates_hz_observed: [50]\n","\n","--- BEFORE: Weather ---\n","  source: Weather (Open-Meteo)\n","  n_files: 1\n","  top_level_keys: ['latitude', 'longitude', 'generationtime_ms', 'utc_offset_seconds', 'timezone', 'timezone_abbreviation', 'elevation', 'hourly_units', 'hourly', 'project_metadata']\n","  hourly_variables: ['time', 'temperature_2m', 'relative_humidity_2m', 'precipitation', 'wind_speed_10m', 'weather_code', 'cloud_cover']\n","  n_hourly_records: 192888\n","  units_declared: {'time': 'iso8601', 'temperature_2m': '°C', 'relative_humidity_2m': '%', 'precipitation': 'mm', 'wind_speed_10m': 'km/h', 'weather_code': 'wmo code', 'cloud_cover': '%'}\n"]}],"source":["## A. Before-snapshot: raw state of all sources\n","\n","# Captured BEFORE any cleaning, so the before/after quality report has a baseline.\n","# This function reads each CSV raw and reports schema/format facts without modifying\n","# anything.\n","\n","def snapshot_csv_folder(folder: Path, source: str) -> dict:\n","    \"\"\"Read every CSV in `folder` raw and return a dict of pre-cleaning facts.\"\"\"\n","    files = sorted(folder.glob(\"*.csv\"))\n","\n","    n_rows = 0\n","    n_nulls = 0\n","    n_dupes = 0\n","    column_sets = []\n","    label_dtypes = set()\n","    subject_id_dtypes = set()\n","    sampling_rates = []\n","\n","    for f in files:\n","        df = pd.read_csv(f)\n","        n_rows += len(df)\n","        n_nulls += int(df.isnull().sum().sum())\n","        n_dupes += int(df.duplicated().sum())\n","        column_sets.append(tuple(df.columns))\n","\n","        # subject_id will be derived from the filename — record what dtype\n","        # the filename would imply if used as-is\n","        stem = f.stem\n","        subject_id_dtypes.add(\"str\" if not stem.isdigit() else \"int\")\n","\n","        if \"label\" in df.columns:\n","            label_dtypes.add(str(df[\"label\"].dtype))\n","\n","        # Infer sampling rate from timestamp median delta\n","        if \"timestamp\" in df.columns:\n","            ts = pd.to_datetime(df[\"timestamp\"], errors=\"coerce\")\n","            med = ts.diff().dt.total_seconds().median()\n","            if med and med > 0:\n","                sampling_rates.append(round(1 / med))\n","\n","    return {\n","        \"source\": source,\n","        \"n_files\": len(files),\n","        \"n_rows\": n_rows,\n","        \"n_nulls\": n_nulls,\n","        \"n_duplicates\": n_dupes,\n","        \"distinct_column_signatures\": len(set(column_sets)),\n","        \"label_dtypes_observed\": sorted(label_dtypes),\n","        \"subject_id_dtype_implied_by_filename\": sorted(subject_id_dtypes),\n","        \"sampling_rates_hz_observed\": sorted(set(sampling_rates)),\n","    }\n","\n","print(\"Snapshotting raw HARTH...\")\n","before_harth = snapshot_csv_folder(HARTH_PATH, \"HARTH\")\n","\n","print(\"Snapshotting raw HAR70+...\")\n","before_har70 = snapshot_csv_folder(HAR70_PATH, \"HAR70+\")\n","\n","print(\"Snapshotting raw Weather JSON...\")\n","with open(WEATHER_RAW) as fh:\n","    raw_weather = json.load(fh)\n","\n","before_weather = {\n","    \"source\": \"Weather (Open-Meteo)\",\n","    \"n_files\": 1,\n","    \"top_level_keys\": list(raw_weather.keys()),\n","    \"hourly_variables\": list(raw_weather[\"hourly\"].keys()),\n","    \"n_hourly_records\": len(raw_weather[\"hourly\"][\"time\"]),\n","    \"units_declared\": raw_weather.get(\"hourly_units\", {}),\n","}\n","\n","before_stats = {\"HARTH\": before_harth, \"HAR70+\": before_har70, \"Weather\": before_weather}\n","\n","for k, v in before_stats.items():\n","    print(f\"\\n--- BEFORE: {k} ---\")\n","    for kk, vv in v.items():\n","        print(f\"  {kk}: {vv}\")"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"0saAUO52eWo3"},"source":["Captures the raw state of all sources as a baseline. This lets us prove exactly what changed during cleaning."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":9,"metadata":{"id":"TG-ITiiieYt3","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070201413,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":5,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}}},"outputs":[],"source":["## B. Schema standardization: column whitelist + timestamp + subject_id\n","\n","# Decision: apply a whitelist of the 8 expected columns at load time.\n","# Alternatives considered: keep all columns (rejected — pollutes data with stray\n","# index columns) and drop only known stray names (rejected — brittle).\n","\n","EXPECTED_COLS_RAW = [\n","    \"timestamp\",\n","    \"back_x\", \"back_y\", \"back_z\",\n","    \"thigh_x\", \"thigh_y\", \"thigh_z\",\n","    \"label\",\n","]\n","\n","def load_single_file(filepath: Path) -> pd.DataFrame:\n","    \"\"\"Load one accelerometer CSV with the schema whitelist applied.\"\"\"\n","    df = pd.read_csv(filepath)\n","\n","    # Drop any column not in our whitelist, log what was removed\n","    extra = [c for c in df.columns if c not in EXPECTED_COLS_RAW]\n","    if extra:\n","        print(f\"    {filepath.name}: dropping extra columns {extra}\")\n","        df = df.drop(columns=extra)\n","\n","    # Fail loudly if required columns are missing\n","    missing = [c for c in EXPECTED_COLS_RAW if c not in df.columns]\n","    if missing:\n","        raise ValueError(f\"{filepath.name}: missing required columns {missing}\")\n","\n","    # Parse timestamp into datetime64, attach subject_id from filename\n","    df[\"timestamp\"]  = pd.to_datetime(df[\"timestamp\"], errors=\"raise\")\n","    df[\"subject_id\"] = filepath.stem\n","\n","    return df"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"YwTRHS0Fed_n"},"source":["This code cleans and standardizes each CSV file when it is loaded.\n","It does five main things:\n","- Defines the exact columns that should exist in the raw dataset (timestamp, sensor values, and label).\n","- Reads one CSV file into a table.\n","- Removes any extra unwanted columns not in the approved list, such as accidental index columns.\n","- Checks that all required columns are present. If any are missing, it stops and gives an error.\n","- Converts the timestamp column into proper date/time format and creates a subject_id column using the file name.\n","\n","In short, it makes sure every file has the same clean structure before combining them."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":10,"metadata":{"id":"Y68XhbZ5emAZ","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070223640,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":22225,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}},"outputId":"e1ffcbbc-a9b0-4030-9d25-7860099a37fa"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["\n","Loading HARTH...\n","    S006.csv: detected 100Hz -> downsampling to 50Hz\n","    S015.csv: dropping extra columns ['index']\n","    S021.csv: dropping extra columns ['index']\n","    S023.csv: dropping extra columns ['Unnamed: 0']\n","  HARTH: 6,256,974 rows, 22 subjects\n","\n","Loading HAR70+...\n","  HAR70+: 2,259,597 rows, 18 subjects\n"]}],"source":["## C. Sampling rate normalization — downsample to 50Hz\n","\n","# Decision: detect each file's rate from median timestamp delta. Downsample\n","# to 50Hz if higher. Only affects HARTH S006 (recorded at 100Hz).\n","# Alternative considered: upsample to 100Hz (rejected — fabricates samples).\n","\n","TARGET_HZ = 50\n","\n","def detect_sampling_rate(df: pd.DataFrame) -> int:\n","    \"\"\"Estimate Hz from median time delta. Robust to occasional gaps.\"\"\"\n","    median_dt = df[\"timestamp\"].diff().dt.total_seconds().median()\n","    return round(1 / median_dt)\n","\n","def downsample_to_target(df: pd.DataFrame, original_hz: int, target_hz: int) -> pd.DataFrame:\n","    \"\"\"Take every n-th row. Only used when original > target.\"\"\"\n","    if original_hz <= target_hz:\n","        return df\n","    step = int(original_hz / target_hz)\n","    return df.iloc[::step].reset_index(drop=True)\n","\n","def load_dataset(folder: Path, source: str) -> pd.DataFrame:\n","    \"\"\"Load every CSV in `folder`, apply schema + sampling standardization.\"\"\"\n","    print(f\"\\nLoading {source}...\")\n","    frames = []\n","\n","    for f in sorted(folder.glob(\"*.csv\")):\n","        df = load_single_file(f)\n","\n","        hz = detect_sampling_rate(df)\n","        if hz != TARGET_HZ:\n","            print(f\"    {f.name}: detected {hz}Hz -> downsampling to {TARGET_HZ}Hz\")\n","            df = downsample_to_target(df, hz, TARGET_HZ)\n","\n","        df[\"source\"] = source\n","        frames.append(df)\n","\n","    out = pd.concat(frames, ignore_index=True)\n","\n","    # Enforce dtypes explicitly — subject_id as string (not mixed) to avoid\n","    # silent bugs after concatenation of HARTH (\"S006\") and HAR70+ (\"501\")\n","    out[\"subject_id\"] = out[\"subject_id\"].astype(str)\n","    out[\"source\"]     = out[\"source\"].astype(str)\n","\n","    print(f\"  {source}: {len(out):,} rows, {out['subject_id'].nunique()} subjects\")\n","    return out\n","\n","harth_df = load_dataset(HARTH_PATH, \"HARTH\")\n","har70_df = load_dataset(HAR70_PATH, \"HAR70+\")"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"Nkeu-eHIeolg"},"source":["\n","\n","Loads all subject CSVs, applies schema standardization, detects and corrects non-50Hz recordings, and tags each with its source cohort. The subject_id dtype is forced to string to keep HARTH's \"S006\" and HAR70+'s \"501\" from producing a mixed-type column after concatenation. S006 is downsampled from 100Hz to 50Hz; three HARTH files drop stray index columns; HAR70+ loads cleanly with no interventions."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":11,"metadata":{"id":"vNwndCzeeyz8","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070223773,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":118,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}},"outputId":"b4ef508a-65ba-40d5-df39-5fe002561f32"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["✓ All timestamps are datetime64[ns] with no NaT values\n","\n","=== Accelerometer range check (expected: roughly within ±8 g) ===\n","\n","HARTH:\n","  back_x      min= -8.000  max=  2.292   [OK]\n","  back_y      min= -4.308  max=  6.492   [OK]\n","  back_z      min= -6.574  max=  4.909   [OK]\n","  thigh_x     min= -8.000  max=  8.000   [OK]\n","  thigh_y     min= -7.997  max=  8.000   [OK]\n","  thigh_z     min= -8.000  max=  8.406   [OK]\n","\n","HAR70+:\n","  back_x      min= -4.333  max=  0.363   [OK]\n","  back_y      min= -2.031  max=  1.577   [OK]\n","  back_z      min= -2.205  max=  1.179   [OK]\n","  thigh_x     min= -7.942  max=  3.395   [OK]\n","  thigh_y     min= -5.143  max=  5.725   [OK]\n","  thigh_z     min= -7.594  max=  3.953   [OK]\n","\n","=== Weather units (declared by Open-Meteo response) ===\n","  time                      iso8601\n","  temperature_2m            °C\n","  relative_humidity_2m      %\n","  precipitation             mm\n","  wind_speed_10m            km/h\n","  weather_code              wmo code\n","  cloud_cover               %\n"]}],"source":["## D. Verification — timestamps and sensor unit ranges\n","\n","# Defense-in-depth: verify the outputs of the previous step before proceeding.\n","\n","# Timestamp dtype + non-null check\n","for name, df in [(\"HARTH\", harth_df), (\"HAR70+\", har70_df)]:\n","    assert df[\"timestamp\"].dtype.kind == \"M\", f\"{name}: timestamp not datetime64\"\n","    assert df[\"timestamp\"].notna().all(), f\"{name}: NaT timestamps after parsing\"\n","print(\"✓ All timestamps are datetime64[ns] with no NaT values\\n\")\n","\n","# Sensor range check — values should be in g units, within ±8g (AX3 sensor range)\n","ACCEL_RANGE_G = (-8, 8)\n","ACCEL_COLS = [\"back_x\", \"back_y\", \"back_z\", \"thigh_x\", \"thigh_y\", \"thigh_z\"]\n","\n","print(\"=== Accelerometer range check (expected: roughly within ±8 g) ===\")\n","for name, df in [(\"HARTH\", harth_df), (\"HAR70+\", har70_df)]:\n","    print(f\"\\n{name}:\")\n","    for c in ACCEL_COLS:\n","        lo, hi = df[c].min(), df[c].max()\n","        status = \"OK\" if (lo >= ACCEL_RANGE_G[0] - 0.5 and hi <= ACCEL_RANGE_G[1] + 0.5) else \"OUT-OF-RANGE\"\n","        print(f\"  {c:10s}  min={lo:7.3f}  max={hi:7.3f}   [{status}]\")\n","\n","# Weather unit declarations\n","print(\"\\n=== Weather units (declared by Open-Meteo response) ===\")\n","for k, v in raw_weather.get(\"hourly_units\", {}).items():\n","    print(f\"  {k:25s} {v}\")"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"J-KRDRWre17r"},"source":["Verifies that timestamps parsed correctly and accelerometer readings fall within the AX3 sensor's ±8g physical envelope. We verify units rather than convert: HAR research conventionally uses g, so rescaling to m/s² would just force every downstream comparison with published work to multiply by 9.80665. The weather API declares its units explicitly: °C, mm, km/h, WMO codes, % so no ambiguity."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":12,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"7aq__ZDFfBao","outputId":"2606cc0a-aa1b-4576-b36f-f8d32af3f166","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070225393,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":1600,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Label coverage check:\n","\n","  HARTH:  unique activities: ['cycling_sit', 'cycling_sit_inactive', 'cycling_stand', 'cycling_stand_inactive', 'lying', 'running', 'shuffling', 'sitting', 'stairs_down', 'stairs_up', 'standing', 'walking']\n","\n","  HAR70+:  unique activities: ['lying', 'shuffling', 'sitting', 'stairs_down', 'stairs_up', 'standing', 'walking']\n"]}],"source":["## E. Activity label mapping — numeric label → human-readable activity\n","\n","# Decision: ADD a string `activity` column derived from numeric `label` using\n","# the official HARTH/HAR70+ codebook. Keep `label` unchanged.\n","# Alternative considered: replace `label` with the string (rejected — loses\n","# the canonical numeric code).\n","\n","# Mapping from numeric label codes to activity names (matches MET lookup keys)\n","CODE_TO_ACTIVITY = {\n","    1:   \"walking\",\n","    2:   \"running\",\n","    3:   \"shuffling\",\n","    4:   \"stairs_up\",\n","    5:   \"stairs_down\",\n","    6:   \"standing\",\n","    7:   \"sitting\",\n","    8:   \"lying\",\n","    13:  \"cycling_sit\",\n","    14:  \"cycling_stand\",\n","    130: \"cycling_sit_inactive\",\n","    140: \"cycling_stand_inactive\",\n","}\n","\n","def add_activity_label(df: pd.DataFrame) -> pd.DataFrame:\n","    \"\"\"Add a string `activity` column derived from `label`. Fail loudly on unknown codes.\"\"\"\n","    df = df.copy()\n","    df[\"activity\"] = df[\"label\"].map(CODE_TO_ACTIVITY)\n","\n","    n_unmapped = df[\"activity\"].isnull().sum()\n","    if n_unmapped > 0:\n","        bad = df[df[\"activity\"].isnull()][\"label\"].unique()\n","        raise ValueError(f\"Unmapped numeric labels found: {bad}\")\n","\n","    return df\n","\n","harth_df = add_activity_label(harth_df)\n","har70_df = add_activity_label(har70_df)\n","\n","print(\"Label coverage check:\")\n","for name, df in [(\"HARTH\", harth_df), (\"HAR70+\", har70_df)]:\n","    print(f\"\\n  {name}:  unique activities: {sorted(df['activity'].unique())}\")"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"-ytCqBEPfD5k"},"source":["Adds a human-readable activity column while preserving the numeric label. A guardrail fails loudly if any numeric code doesn't have a mapping, which prevents silent label drift. HARTH uses all 12 codes; HAR70+ uses only 7 (running and all cycling variants are entirely absent, which has direct implications for cross-cohort comparison and the app's recommendation filtering)."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":13,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"uRYuQLTxfa-6","outputId":"d77d81e8-492b-49da-95cd-abb736a84472","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070225549,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":121,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Weather rows: 192,888\n","Total missing values: 0\n","Hourly continuity: 192,888/192,888  (0 missing hours)\n","\n","✓ No missing values, no temporal gaps — ffill policy not triggered\n","\n","============================================================\n","CLIMATOLOGY PROFILES (lifted from weather_raw.json metadata)\n","============================================================\n","\n","  s1_bulk:\n","    430 hours (years 2016–2016)\n","    applies to: 14 HARTH Session 1 subjects on placeholder 2019-01-12\n","    temperature_c: 2.45 ± 4.61 °C\n","    humidity_pct:  84.4  ± 11.3  %\n","\n","  s2_bulk:\n","    2,190 hours (years 2017–2021)\n","    applies to: 7 HARTH Session 2 subjects on placeholder 2000-01-01\n","    temperature_c: 4.60 ± 4.49 °C\n","    humidity_pct:  80.1  ± 13.6  %\n"]}],"source":["## F. Weather parsing and temporal continuity check\n","\n","# Decision: parse the nested Open-Meteo JSON into a flat table with explicit\n","# dtype casting. Forward-fill any gaps up to 3 hours (short gaps only).\n","# Alternative considered: interpolate long gaps (rejected — fabricates values\n","# over unknown periods).\n","#\n","# Also lifts the pre-computed climatology profiles out of project_metadata\n","# into a DataFrame. These profiles were built by weather_preparation.ipynb\n","# from the same hourly corpus and embedded in the raw JSON, so there is a\n","# single source of truth for the stratified weather attach further down.\n","\n","def parse_weather_json(raw: dict) -> pd.DataFrame:\n","    \"\"\"Nested Open-Meteo JSON → flat DataFrame with explicit dtype casting.\"\"\"\n","    h = raw[\"hourly\"]\n","    df = pd.DataFrame({\n","        \"weather_timestamp\": pd.to_datetime(h[\"time\"]),\n","        \"temperature_c\":     pd.to_numeric(h[\"temperature_2m\"],       errors=\"coerce\"),\n","        \"humidity_pct\":      pd.to_numeric(h[\"relative_humidity_2m\"], errors=\"coerce\"),\n","        \"precipitation_mm\":  pd.to_numeric(h[\"precipitation\"],        errors=\"coerce\"),\n","        \"wind_speed_kmh\":    pd.to_numeric(h[\"wind_speed_10m\"],       errors=\"coerce\"),\n","        \"weather_code\":      pd.to_numeric(h[\"weather_code\"],         errors=\"coerce\"),\n","        \"cloud_cover_pct\":   pd.to_numeric(h[\"cloud_cover\"],          errors=\"coerce\"),\n","    })\n","    return df\n","\n","\n","def lift_climatology_table(raw: dict) -> pd.DataFrame:\n","    \"\"\"Extract project_metadata.climatology_profiles → long-form DataFrame.\n","\n","    Each row is one profile (s1_bulk, s2_bulk) with flat columns ready for\n","    the stratified attach to read. Fails loudly if the rich-JSON metadata\n","    is absent.\n","    \"\"\"\n","    if \"project_metadata\" not in raw:\n","        raise ValueError(\n","            \"weather_raw.json has no 'project_metadata' block — \"\n","            \"run weather_preparation.ipynb first.\"\n","        )\n","    profiles = raw[\"project_metadata\"][\"climatology_profiles\"]\n","    rows = []\n","    for key, prof in profiles.items():\n","        row = {\n","            \"weather_lookup_key\":  key,\n","            \"n_hours_in_profile\":  prof[\"n_hours_in_profile\"],\n","            \"year_min\":            prof[\"year_min\"],\n","            \"year_max\":            prof[\"year_max\"],\n","            \"applies_to\":          prof[\"applies_to\"],\n","            \"rationale\":           prof[\"rationale\"],\n","            \"weather_code_mode\":   prof[\"weather_code_mode\"],\n","        }\n","        for var in [\"temperature_c\", \"humidity_pct\", \"precipitation_mm\",\n","                    \"wind_speed_kmh\", \"cloud_cover_pct\"]:\n","            row[f\"{var}_mean\"] = prof[f\"{var}_mean\"]\n","            row[f\"{var}_std\"]  = prof[f\"{var}_std\"]\n","        rows.append(row)\n","    return pd.DataFrame(rows)\n","\n","\n","# --- Parse hourly weather --------------------------------------------------\n","weather_df = parse_weather_json(raw_weather)\n","\n","# Completeness check\n","missing_count = weather_df.isnull().sum().sum()\n","expected_idx  = pd.date_range(weather_df[\"weather_timestamp\"].min(),\n","                              weather_df[\"weather_timestamp\"].max(), freq=\"h\")\n","missing_hours = expected_idx.difference(weather_df[\"weather_timestamp\"])\n","\n","print(f\"Weather rows: {len(weather_df):,}\")\n","print(f\"Total missing values: {missing_count}\")\n","print(f\"Hourly continuity: {len(weather_df):,}/{len(expected_idx):,}  \"\n","      f\"({len(missing_hours)} missing hours)\")\n","\n","# Conditional forward-fill\n","if missing_count > 0 or len(missing_hours) > 0:\n","    print(\"\\n→ Gaps or nulls detected. Applying forward-fill (limit=3h)...\")\n","    cols = [\"temperature_c\", \"humidity_pct\", \"precipitation_mm\",\n","            \"wind_speed_kmh\", \"weather_code\", \"cloud_cover_pct\"]\n","    weather_df = (weather_df.set_index(\"weather_timestamp\")\n","                            .asfreq(\"h\")\n","                            .reset_index())\n","    weather_df[cols] = weather_df[cols].ffill(limit=3)\n","    print(f\"  After ffill: {weather_df.isnull().sum().sum()} values still missing\")\n","else:\n","    print(\"\\n✓ No missing values, no temporal gaps — ffill policy not triggered\")\n","\n","# --- Lift climatology profiles from the rich JSON --------------------------\n","climatology_table = lift_climatology_table(raw_weather)\n","\n","print(\"\\n\" + \"=\" * 60)\n","print(\"CLIMATOLOGY PROFILES (lifted from weather_raw.json metadata)\")\n","print(\"=\" * 60)\n","for _, row in climatology_table.iterrows():\n","    print(f\"\\n  {row['weather_lookup_key']}:\")\n","    print(f\"    {row['n_hours_in_profile']:,} hours \"\n","          f\"(years {row['year_min']}–{row['year_max']})\")\n","    print(f\"    applies to: {row['applies_to']}\")\n","    print(f\"    temperature_c: {row['temperature_c_mean']:.2f} ± \"\n","          f\"{row['temperature_c_std']:.2f} °C\")\n","    print(f\"    humidity_pct:  {row['humidity_pct_mean']:.1f}  ± \"\n","          f\"{row['humidity_pct_std']:.1f}  %\")"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"qn5AoCxJfdsi"},"source":["Parses the nested JSON into a flat table and runs two completeness checks\n","- value-level (nulls?)\n","- time-level (missing hours?)\n","\n","Forward-fill with a 3-hour limit is implemented as a policy even if not triggered on this run: short gaps get the last-known value, longer gaps stay NaN so they don't silently propagate stale weather."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":14,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"ElBXtwBlfsAH","outputId":"b765ac6e-92da-4b4d-9766-1a2cadc0d4fc","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070242937,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":17357,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Missing value report (post-standardization):\n","\n","HARTH:  6,256,974 rows\n","            n_null  pct_null\n","timestamp        0       0.0\n","back_x           0       0.0\n","back_y           0       0.0\n","back_z           0       0.0\n","thigh_x          0       0.0\n","thigh_y          0       0.0\n","thigh_z          0       0.0\n","label            0       0.0\n","subject_id       0       0.0\n","source           0       0.0\n","activity         0       0.0\n","\n","HAR70+:  2,259,597 rows\n","            n_null  pct_null\n","timestamp        0       0.0\n","back_x           0       0.0\n","back_y           0       0.0\n","back_z           0       0.0\n","thigh_x          0       0.0\n","thigh_y          0       0.0\n","thigh_z          0       0.0\n","label            0       0.0\n","subject_id       0       0.0\n","source           0       0.0\n","activity         0       0.0\n","\n","HARTH:\n","  exact-row duplicates:                0\n","  (subject_id, timestamp) duplicates:  0\n","\n","HAR70+:\n","  exact-row duplicates:                0\n","  (subject_id, timestamp) duplicates:  0\n","\n","Weather:\n","  exact-row duplicates:                0\n","  weather_timestamp duplicates:        0\n"]}],"source":["## G. Missing value and duplicate handling\n","\n","# Decision: per-source policy. Activity CSVs have zero nulls — no imputation\n","# needed. Weather handled above. For duplicates: check both exact-row and\n","# composite-key duplicates; dedupe by composite key if found.\n","\n","def missing_value_report(df: pd.DataFrame, name: str) -> None:\n","    \"\"\"Report null counts per column — diagnostic only, no modification.\"\"\"\n","    rep = pd.DataFrame({\n","        \"n_null\":   df.isnull().sum(),\n","        \"pct_null\": (df.isnull().mean() * 100).round(4),\n","    })\n","    print(f\"\\n{name}:  {len(df):,} rows\")\n","    print(rep.to_string())\n","\n","print(\"Missing value report (post-standardization):\")\n","missing_value_report(harth_df, \"HARTH\")\n","missing_value_report(har70_df, \"HAR70+\")\n","\n","# Duplicate handling — two different definitions catch different error classes\n","def duplicate_report(df: pd.DataFrame, name: str) -> dict:\n","    n_exact = int(df.duplicated().sum())\n","    n_composite = int(df.duplicated(subset=[\"subject_id\", \"timestamp\"]).sum())\n","    print(f\"\\n{name}:\")\n","    print(f\"  exact-row duplicates:                {n_exact}\")\n","    print(f\"  (subject_id, timestamp) duplicates:  {n_composite}\")\n","    return {\"exact\": n_exact, \"composite\": n_composite}\n","\n","dup_harth   = duplicate_report(harth_df,   \"HARTH\")\n","dup_har70   = duplicate_report(har70_df,   \"HAR70+\")\n","dup_weather = {\n","    \"exact\":     int(weather_df.duplicated().sum()),\n","    \"composite\": int(weather_df.duplicated(subset=[\"weather_timestamp\"]).sum()),\n","}\n","print(f\"\\nWeather:\")\n","print(f\"  exact-row duplicates:                {dup_weather['exact']}\")\n","print(f\"  weather_timestamp duplicates:        {dup_weather['composite']}\")\n","\n","# Apply dedup policy — no-op if zero duplicates, but documents what we'd do\n","if dup_harth[\"composite\"] > 0:\n","    harth_df = harth_df.drop_duplicates(subset=[\"subject_id\", \"timestamp\"], keep=\"first\")\n","if dup_har70[\"composite\"] > 0:\n","    har70_df = har70_df.drop_duplicates(subset=[\"subject_id\", \"timestamp\"], keep=\"first\")\n","if dup_weather[\"composite\"] > 0:\n","    weather_df = weather_df.drop_duplicates(subset=[\"weather_timestamp\"], keep=\"first\")"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"0hjEny4vfvFP"},"source":["Reports nulls and duplicates for all three sources. Accelerometer data has zero nulls in both cohorts. Both duplicate definitions are checked: exact-row (file-level copy-paste errors) and composite-key `(subject_id, timestamp)` (sensor double-emission). Running the check and reporting zero is more valuable than skipping it, as it proves verification happened."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":15,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"UONOBmhugCFO","outputId":"d2a4c513-69c1-4f2e-bd69-4e94f61d83bb","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070243971,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":1032,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["HARTH clipping:\n","  flagged 188 clipped rows (0.0030% of 6,256,974)\n","HAR70+ clipping:\n","  flagged 0 clipped rows (0.0000% of 2,259,597)\n"]}],"source":["## H. Outlier and anomaly handling — clipping + time gaps\n","\n","# F.1 — Sensor clipping: FLAG, don't drop. Clipping concentrates in high-intensity\n","# activities; dropping would systematically under-represent them.\n","# F.2 — Global IQR outlier removal: REJECTED with evidence (see chart below).\n","# F.3 — Time gaps > 1s: FLAG, don't drop. Preserves auditability.\n","\n","CLIP_THRESHOLD_G = 7.99  # 0.01g tolerance accounts for floating-point representation\n","\n","def flag_clipped(df: pd.DataFrame, threshold: float = CLIP_THRESHOLD_G) -> pd.DataFrame:\n","    \"\"\"Add an 'is_clipped' column marking rows where any axis hit the sensor limit.\"\"\"\n","    df = df.copy()\n","    is_clipped = pd.Series(False, index=df.index)\n","    for c in ACCEL_COLS:\n","        is_clipped |= df[c].abs() >= threshold\n","    df[\"is_clipped\"] = is_clipped\n","    print(f\"  flagged {int(is_clipped.sum()):,} clipped rows \"\n","          f\"({is_clipped.mean()*100:.4f}% of {len(df):,})\")\n","    return df\n","\n","print(\"HARTH clipping:\")\n","harth_df = flag_clipped(harth_df)\n","print(\"HAR70+ clipping:\")\n","har70_df = flag_clipped(har70_df)"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"5DcM-mxBgEtb"},"source":["Flags rows where any sensor axis hit the ±8g hardware ceiling. Clipping concentrates in high-intensity activities (running, stair descents), dropping would systematically under-represent exactly the activities most relevant for energy-expenditure analytics. Expected result: ~188 rows flagged in HARTH (running), zero in HAR70+ (no running, no rail-hitting)."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":16,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":457},"id":"sBlMGtWcgNSM","outputId":"97a66166-fdfc-4473-d816-23fe82451c25","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070253349,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":9376,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 1000x450 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"source":["## H.2 — Evidence for rejecting global IQR outlier removal\n","\n","# Each activity has a distinct, legitimate range. Trimming global IQR fences\n","# would systematically remove high-intensity activities (running, stairs) —\n","# treating legitimate physical movement as noise.\n","\n","combined_for_plot = pd.concat([harth_df, har70_df], ignore_index=True)\n","plot_activities = [\"lying\", \"sitting\", \"standing\", \"walking\", \"running\"]\n","plot_activities = [a for a in plot_activities if a in combined_for_plot[\"activity\"].unique()]\n","\n","fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 4.5))\n","for act in plot_activities:\n","    subset = combined_for_plot[combined_for_plot[\"activity\"] == act][\"back_x\"]\n","    ax.hist(subset, bins=120, alpha=0.45, label=act, density=True)\n","ax.set_xlabel(\"back_x acceleration (g)\")\n","ax.set_ylabel(\"density\")\n","ax.set_title(\"back_x distribution by activity — each activity has its own legitimate range\")\n","ax.legend()\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.show()\n","\n","del combined_for_plot"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"aNp2YM2WgPyA"},"source":["Evidence chart that justifies rejecting global IQR filtering. Each activity has its own signature range: lying and standing cluster tightly, running spreads widely. A global IQR would flag running as \"outliers\" even though it's legitimate movement. Per-activity IQR was also rejected because within-activity variation (subject style, intensity) is exactly what the pipeline needs to measure."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":17,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"xRSa606dgRwF","outputId":"1c1c46a9-10d1-4eb8-ce9f-11a615a374bc","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070256528,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":3177,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["HARTH time-gap flagging:\n","  flagged 569 rows following gaps > 1.0s\n","HAR70+ time-gap flagging:\n","  flagged 249 rows following gaps > 1.0s\n"]}],"source":["## H.3 — Time gap flagging\n","\n","# Threshold: 1 second. Below that, sensor was likely buffering. Above that,\n","# a meaningful chunk of activity is missing.\n","\n","GAP_THRESHOLD_S = 1.0\n","\n","def flag_time_gaps(df: pd.DataFrame, max_gap_seconds: float = GAP_THRESHOLD_S) -> pd.DataFrame:\n","    \"\"\"Flag rows that follow a time gap greater than the threshold.\"\"\"\n","    df = df.sort_values([\"subject_id\", \"timestamp\"]).reset_index(drop=True)\n","    df[\"time_diff\"] = df.groupby(\"subject_id\")[\"timestamp\"].diff().dt.total_seconds()\n","    # First row per subject has NaN diff — set to 0 so it's never flagged\n","    df[\"time_diff\"] = df[\"time_diff\"].fillna(0)\n","    df[\"after_gap\"] = df[\"time_diff\"] > max_gap_seconds\n","    print(f\"  flagged {int(df['after_gap'].sum()):,} rows following gaps > {max_gap_seconds}s\")\n","    return df\n","\n","print(\"HARTH time-gap flagging:\")\n","harth_df = flag_time_gaps(harth_df)\n","print(\"HAR70+ time-gap flagging:\")\n","har70_df = flag_time_gaps(har70_df)"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"kkASdLWlgUIt"},"source":["Flags rows immediately after time gaps > 1 second — meaning the sensor stopped recording mid-stream before resuming. The flag doesn't drop anything; downstream code decides whether temporal continuity matters for its specific computation (e.g., gait periodicity cares; mean acceleration doesn't)."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":18,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"stUUIGmngW8u","outputId":"f285485a-846c-42d5-a71c-2fd11c912646","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070256564,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":34,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Weather sentinel / range scan:\n","  temperature_c         observed [  -29.40,    31.30]  expected [-30, 35]  OK\n","  humidity_pct          observed [   15.00,   100.00]  expected [0, 100]  OK\n","  precipitation_mm      observed [    0.00,     8.00]  expected [0, 100]  OK\n","  wind_speed_kmh        observed [    0.00,    45.20]  expected [0, 200]  OK\n","  weather_code          observed [    0.00,    75.00]  expected [0, 99]  OK\n","  cloud_cover_pct       observed [    0.00,   100.00]  expected [0, 100]  OK\n"]}],"source":["## I. Weather sentinel value and range scan\n","\n","# Verify every weather variable is within physical bounds for Trondheim.\n","# Catches sentinel values (-999 for missing) and unit errors (Fahrenheit in\n","# a Celsius column).\n","\n","WEATHER_RANGES = {\n","    \"temperature_c\":    (-30, 35),\n","    \"humidity_pct\":     (0, 100),\n","    \"precipitation_mm\": (0, 100),\n","    \"wind_speed_kmh\":   (0, 200),\n","    \"weather_code\":     (0, 99),\n","    \"cloud_cover_pct\":  (0, 100),\n","}\n","\n","print(\"Weather sentinel / range scan:\")\n","all_ok = True\n","for col, (lo, hi) in WEATHER_RANGES.items():\n","    actual_lo = weather_df[col].min()\n","    actual_hi = weather_df[col].max()\n","    n_violations = ((weather_df[col] < lo) | (weather_df[col] > hi)).sum()\n","    status = \"OK\" if n_violations == 0 else f\"FAIL ({n_violations} out of range)\"\n","    if n_violations > 0:\n","        all_ok = False\n","    print(f\"  {col:20s}  observed [{actual_lo:>8.2f}, {actual_hi:>8.2f}]  \"\n","          f\"expected [{lo}, {hi}]  {status}\")\n","\n","assert all_ok, \"Weather sentinel scan failed — investigate before proceeding\""]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"_9HpXXZwgaJ2"},"source":["Physical-plausibility check on every weather variable. Defends against sentinel values (−999) that some APIs use for missing data, and against silent unit errors. Expected: all ranges pass. Temperature span reflects Trondheim's sub-Arctic climate; precipitation peaks around 8mm/hour; wind tops out below 50 km/h."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":19,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"Ne9wbXWigZkD","outputId":"6640708e-5156-483b-9478-e0b4fde89781","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070263220,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":6653,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["\n","Validating HARTH (6,256,974 rows)...\n","  ✓ Rule 1 (schema) passed\n","  ✓ Rule 2 (accelerometer range ±8 g) passed\n","  ✓ Rule 3 (categorical values) passed\n","  ✓ Rule 4 (timestamps monotonic per subject) passed\n","  ✓ Rule 5 (identity / unique composite key) passed\n","\n","Validating HAR70+ (2,259,597 rows)...\n","  ✓ Rule 1 (schema) passed\n","  ✓ Rule 2 (accelerometer range ±8 g) passed\n","  ✓ Rule 3 (categorical values) passed\n","  ✓ Rule 4 (timestamps monotonic per subject) passed\n","  ✓ Rule 5 (identity / unique composite key) passed\n","\n","Validating Weather (192,888 rows)...\n","  ✓ Schema passed\n","  ✓ Range passed\n","  ✓ Temporal passed\n","\n","✓ All validation rules passed\n"]}],"source":["## J. Data validation rules — enforced contract for cleaned outputs\n","\n","# Five invariants the cleaned accelerometer data must satisfy.\n","# Implemented as assertions so any violation halts the pipeline immediately.\n","\n","def validate_activity_frame(df: pd.DataFrame, name: str) -> None:\n","    \"\"\"Run all five validation rules on a cleaned activity dataframe.\"\"\"\n","    print(f\"\\nValidating {name} ({len(df):,} rows)...\")\n","\n","    # Rule 1 — Schema\n","    expected = {\"timestamp\", \"back_x\", \"back_y\", \"back_z\",\n","                \"thigh_x\", \"thigh_y\", \"thigh_z\", \"label\",\n","                \"subject_id\", \"source\", \"activity\",\n","                \"is_clipped\", \"time_diff\", \"after_gap\"}\n","    assert expected.issubset(df.columns), \\\n","        f\"  Schema FAIL: missing {expected - set(df.columns)}\"\n","    assert df[\"timestamp\"].dtype.kind == \"M\", \\\n","        \"  Schema FAIL: timestamp not datetime64\"\n","    assert df[\"subject_id\"].dtype == object or pd.api.types.is_string_dtype(df[\"subject_id\"]), \\\n","        f\"  Schema FAIL: subject_id not string-like\"\n","    assert pd.api.types.is_bool_dtype(df[\"is_clipped\"]), \\\n","        \"  Schema FAIL: is_clipped not bool\"\n","    assert pd.api.types.is_bool_dtype(df[\"after_gap\"]), \\\n","        \"  Schema FAIL: after_gap not bool\"\n","    print(\"  ✓ Rule 1 (schema) passed\")\n","\n","    # Rule 2 — Range\n","    for c in ACCEL_COLS:\n","        lo, hi = df[c].min(), df[c].max()\n","        assert ACCEL_RANGE_G[0] - 0.5 <= lo and hi <= ACCEL_RANGE_G[1] + 0.5, \\\n","            f\"  Range FAIL on {c}: [{lo}, {hi}]\"\n","    print(\"  ✓ Rule 2 (accelerometer range ±8 g) passed\")\n","\n","    # Rule 3 — Categoricals\n","    unknown_act = set(df[\"activity\"].unique()) - set(CODE_TO_ACTIVITY.values())\n","    assert not unknown_act, f\"  Activity FAIL: unknown values {unknown_act}\"\n","    assert set(df[\"source\"].unique()).issubset({\"HARTH\", \"HAR70+\"}), \\\n","        f\"  Source FAIL: {df['source'].unique()}\"\n","    print(\"  ✓ Rule 3 (categorical values) passed\")\n","\n","    # Rule 4 — Temporal monotonicity per subject\n","    bad_subjects = []\n","    for sid, sub in df.groupby(\"subject_id\"):\n","        if not sub[\"timestamp\"].is_monotonic_increasing:\n","            bad_subjects.append(sid)\n","    assert not bad_subjects, \\\n","        f\"  Temporal FAIL: non-monotonic timestamps in subjects {bad_subjects[:5]}\"\n","    print(\"  ✓ Rule 4 (timestamps monotonic per subject) passed\")\n","\n","    # Rule 5 — Identity / unique composite key\n","    assert df[\"subject_id\"].notna().all() and (df[\"subject_id\"] != \"\").all(), \\\n","        \"  Identity FAIL: blank subject_id\"\n","    n_dup = df.duplicated(subset=[\"subject_id\", \"timestamp\"]).sum()\n","    assert n_dup == 0, f\"  Identity FAIL: {n_dup} composite-key duplicates\"\n","    print(\"  ✓ Rule 5 (identity / unique composite key) passed\")\n","\n","\n","def validate_weather_frame(df: pd.DataFrame) -> None:\n","    \"\"\"Run schema, range, and temporal checks on the cleaned weather dataframe.\"\"\"\n","    print(f\"\\nValidating Weather ({len(df):,} rows)...\")\n","\n","    expected = {\"weather_timestamp\", \"temperature_c\", \"humidity_pct\",\n","                \"precipitation_mm\", \"wind_speed_kmh\", \"weather_code\",\n","                \"cloud_cover_pct\"}\n","    assert expected.issubset(df.columns), \\\n","        f\"  Schema FAIL: missing {expected - set(df.columns)}\"\n","    assert df[\"weather_timestamp\"].dtype.kind == \"M\", \\\n","        \"  Schema FAIL: weather_timestamp not datetime64\"\n","    print(\"  ✓ Schema passed\")\n","\n","    for col, (lo, hi) in WEATHER_RANGES.items():\n","        v_lo, v_hi = df[col].min(), df[col].max()\n","        assert lo <= v_lo and v_hi <= hi, f\"  Range FAIL on {col}: [{v_lo}, {v_hi}]\"\n","    print(\"  ✓ Range passed\")\n","\n","    assert df[\"weather_timestamp\"].is_monotonic_increasing, \"  Temporal FAIL: not monotonic\"\n","    assert df[\"weather_timestamp\"].duplicated().sum() == 0, \"  Temporal FAIL: duplicates\"\n","    print(\"  ✓ Temporal passed\")\n","\n","validate_activity_frame(harth_df, \"HARTH\")\n","validate_activity_frame(har70_df, \"HAR70+\")\n","validate_weather_frame(weather_df)\n","print(\"\\n✓ All validation rules passed\")"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"g2ZA7ltRgdE2"},"source":["Codifies the data quality contract the cleaned outputs must satisfy. Five rules for accelerometer data: schema, range, categorical, temporal (per subject), identity. Three rules for weather: schema, range, temporal. Any violation raises an AssertionError, halting the notebook — a lightweight equivalent of a great-expectations suite."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":20,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":1000},"id":"RTChVwKmghaq","outputId":"97b4e217-c903-4ad5-a7e9-3f25462b0ce4","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070