ther_df.to_csv(out_weather, index=False)\n","print(f\"Saved: {out_weather}  ({out_weather.stat().st_size / 1e6:.1f} MB)\")"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"tUyVdMcggsWr"},"source":["Writes the cleaned frames to Data/cleaned/ — the final deliverable of this notebook. Four outputs: HARTH alone, HAR70+ alone, both combined (convenience for cross-cohort work), and weather. CSV was chosen over Parquet for low friction — any grader or teammate can open these in any tool. Parquet would be 5–10× smaller and dtype-preserving; a one-line change if the pipeline later grows."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"id":"5i1J_NkKguad","executionInfo":{"status":"aborted","timestamp":1777070277263,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":202254,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}}},"outputs":[],"source":["## N. Handoff to Section 4.4\n","\n","# The cleaned outputs above are ready for Section 4.4 — Data Processing for Analytics.\n","# The processing pipeline picks up from here:\n","#\n","#   1. Windowing (notebook 02)     — segment 50Hz stream into 2-second windows.\n","#                                     Rows with after_gap=True flow into has_gap.\n","#   2. Window-level features       — compute mean/std/min/max per axis per window.\n","#   3. Intensity calibration       — derive intensity_percentile + adjusted_met per window.\n","#   4. Calorie rate (weight-free)  — compute cal_per_kg = adjusted_met × duration_hr.\n","#   5. Storage load (notebook 05)  — push fact table + dimensions into SQLite star schema.\n","#\n","# Then Section 4.5 runs the analytical SQL queries and interprets the results."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"-DE1Wy1IgyUv"},"source":["Explicit contract between cleaning (this notebook) and the downstream processing stage. Each step is implemented in a dedicated notebook so the pipeline stays modular. The handoff is file-based: this notebook ends when the cleaned CSVs hit disk, and every downstream notebook reads from those files rather than regenerating intermediate state."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"HYJ-ONREy5NR"},"source":["# Section 4.4: Data Processing for Analytics"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"brrho697g_dZ"},"source":["## Section 4.4.1: Windowing and Feature Extraction\n","\n","The cleaned 50Hz stream is segmented into 2-second windows. Each window receives 24 sensor-derived features: mean, standard deviation, min, and max per axis (back and thigh × x, y, z). Each window also carries its activity label, subject ID, source cohort, label purity, and gap status.\n","\n","This notebook takes the cleaned 50Hz accelerometer streams produced by\n","`01_cleaning_transformation.ipynb` and segments them into fixed-length\n","2-second windows. Each window is then summarized by a set of statistical\n","features computed from the raw sensor readings.\n","\n","## Relationship to other notebooks\n","- **Reads from:** `Data/cleaned/combined_cleaned.csv`\n","- **Writes to:** `Data/cleaned/windowed_2s.csv`\n","- **Consumed by:** `03_intensity_calibration.ipynb`\n","\n","## Why windowing?\n","The raw data is a continuous stream of 50 sensor readings per second per axis.\n","This is too fine-grained for activity-level analysis — a single reading tells\n","us nothing about what activity was happening. By grouping readings into\n","2-second windows and summarizing each window statistically, we get:\n","\n","- A consistent, comparable unit across subjects and activities\n","- A dramatic reduction in data volume (from ~8.5M rows to ~85k)\n","- Features that capture movement intensity, not just instantaneous acceleration\n","\n","## Output\n","A single table where each row represents one 2-second window, with:\n","- Identity: subject_id, source, window_start, window_end\n","- Label: activity, label_purity\n","- 24 sensor features: mean/std/min/max for each of 6 axes\n","- Quality flags: has_gap, window_duration"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":25,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"tm9rotQNhEob","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070285377,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":29,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}},"outputId":"8dd22e58-19ba-4348-d7bc-0b13f52b23cd"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Input:  /content/drive/MyDrive/Data Processing Project/Data/cleaned/combined_cleaned.csv\n","Output: /content/drive/MyDrive/Data Processing Project/Data/cleaned/windowed_2s.csv\n"]}],"source":["# Input: cleaned combined dataset from the cleaning notebook\n","COMBINED_IN = CLEAN_DIR / \"combined_cleaned.csv\"\n","\n","# Output: windowed fact table\n","WINDOWED_OUT = CLEAN_DIR / \"windowed_2s.csv\"\n","\n","# Sanity check — fail loud if the cleaning notebook hasn't been run\n","assert COMBINED_IN.exists(), \\\n","    f\"combined_cleaned.csv not found — run 01_cleaning_transformation first\"\n","\n","print(f\"Input:  {COMBINED_IN}\")\n","print(f\"Output: {WINDOWED_OUT}\")"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"tixY7Ja9hGuN"},"source":["\n","\n","Resolves paths and verifies the cleaned input exists. No network access in this notebook — everything comes from local disk."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":27,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"Pw3RdWEshJiq","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070356271,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":28724,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}},"outputId":"a16a0f1e-c547-4974-a802-4c4e933db7c9"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Loading combined_cleaned.csv...\n"]},{"output_type":"stream","name":"stderr","text":["/tmp/ipykernel_11043/44377383.py:7: DtypeWarning: Columns (8) have mixed types. Specify dtype option on import or set low_memory=False.\n","  df = pd.read_csv(COMBINED_IN, parse_dates=[\"timestamp\"])\n"]},{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["  rows:      8,516,571\n","  subjects:  40\n","  activities: 12\n","  sources:   ['HARTH', 'HAR70+']\n"]}],"source":["## A. Load cleaned data\n","\n","# The combined_cleaned.csv contains both HARTH and HAR70+ stacked, already\n","# standardized to 50Hz with quality flags applied.\n","\n","print(\"Loading combined_cleaned.csv...\")\n","df = pd.read_csv(COMBINED_IN, parse_dates=[\"timestamp\"])\n","\n","# Enforce dtypes that CSV round-trip would have lost\n","df[\"subject_id\"] = df[\"subject_id\"].astype(str)\n","df[\"source\"]     = df[\"source\"].astype(str)\n","df[\"is_clipped\"] = df[\"is_clipped\"].astype(bool)\n","df[\"after_gap\"]  = df[\"after_gap\"].astype(bool)\n","\n","print(f\"  rows:      {len(df):,}\")\n","print(f\"  subjects:  {df['subject_id'].nunique()}\")\n","print(f\"  activities: {df['activity'].nunique()}\")\n","print(f\"  sources:   {df['source'].unique().tolist()}\")"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"NsqVSpFohXJe"},"source":["Loads the cleaned data and re-enforces dtypes that CSV serialization would have lost (booleans become strings, subject_id could become int, etc.). After this cell, the dataframe is ready for windowing."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":29,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"UU1i6FWIhYp0","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070364043,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":22,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}},"outputId":"6a563d99-8f8f-4dae-afe4-95436cae3c3e"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Window length:            2s\n","Expected samples/window:  100\n","Minimum samples accepted: 95 (95%)\n","Feature columns per window: 24\n"]}],"source":["## B. Windowing configuration\n","\n","# Window length in seconds. At 50Hz, this means 100 samples per window.\n","WINDOW_SECONDS = 2\n","\n","# Sampling rate set in the cleaning notebook\n","SAMPLING_HZ = 50\n","\n","# Expected samples per window — used to flag under-filled windows\n","EXPECTED_SAMPLES_PER_WINDOW = WINDOW_SECONDS * SAMPLING_HZ\n","\n","# Tolerance for \"complete\" windows. Anything below this is flagged as gap-affected.\n","# We allow 5% tolerance for windows that straddle a tiny sensor hiccup.\n","COMPLETENESS_TOLERANCE = 0.95\n","MIN_SAMPLES_PER_WINDOW = int(EXPECTED_SAMPLES_PER_WINDOW * COMPLETENESS_TOLERANCE)\n","\n","# Sensor columns — the 6 accelerometer axes we'll summarize per window\n","ACCEL_COLS = [\"back_x\", \"back_y\", \"back_z\", \"thigh_x\", \"thigh_y\", \"thigh_z\"]\n","\n","# Features to compute per axis per window\n","FEATURE_FUNCS = [\"mean\", \"std\", \"min\", \"max\"]\n","\n","print(f\"Window length:            {WINDOW_SECONDS}s\")\n","print(f\"Expected samples/window:  {EXPECTED_SAMPLES_PER_WINDOW}\")\n","print(f\"Minimum samples accepted: {MIN_SAMPLES_PER_WINDOW} ({COMPLETENESS_TOLERANCE*100:.0f}%)\")\n","print(f\"Feature columns per window: {len(ACCEL_COLS) * len(FEATURE_FUNCS)}\")"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"ZSdf42QUhbgZ"},"source":["Configuration for the windowing step. We chose 2-second windows because it's long enough to capture a full walking cycle or cycling rotation but short enough that most windows contain a single activity. The 5% completeness tolerance (95 samples minimum out of 100) lets us keep windows that straddle tiny sensor hiccups while flagging anything larger as gap-affected."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":30,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"EUTKicPvhdRI","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070364093,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":49,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}},"outputId":"574df123-555a-4b9b-e6c4-75af108e362e"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["summarize_window() defined\n"]}],"source":["## C. Label assignment and purity — decision\n","\n","# Each 2-second window contains ~100 raw samples, each with its own label.\n","# In practice, 97%+ of windows are single-label (the person didn't switch\n","# activities mid-window). But some windows DO span transitions.\n","#\n","# Decision: assign the most common label, record the purity.\n","# Alternative 1 — drop mixed windows: rejected. Loses transition data that\n","#                 actually carries information (e.g., sitting→standing).\n","# Alternative 2 — accept any label: rejected. Silently introduces noise.\n","# Our approach: keep the window, label it by majority, flag purity for\n","# downstream filtering.\n","\n","def summarize_window(window_samples: pd.DataFrame) -> dict:\n","    \"\"\"Summarize one window of raw samples into a single row of features.\"\"\"\n","\n","    # Identity\n","    subject_id = window_samples[\"subject_id\"].iloc[0]\n","    source     = window_samples[\"source\"].iloc[0]\n","\n","    # Window boundaries\n","    window_start = window_samples[\"timestamp\"].min()\n","    window_end   = window_samples[\"timestamp\"].max()\n","\n","    # Actual duration in seconds (should be ~2s, might be more if there's a gap)\n","    window_duration = (window_end - window_start).total_seconds()\n","\n","    # Label: majority vote + purity\n","    label_counts = window_samples[\"activity\"].value_counts()\n","    majority_activity = label_counts.index[0]\n","    label_purity = label_counts.iloc[0] / len(window_samples)\n","\n","    # Also carry the numeric label for the majority activity\n","    majority_label = window_samples.loc[\n","        window_samples[\"activity\"] == majority_activity, \"label\"\n","    ].iloc[0]\n","\n","    # Gap flag — true if the window crosses a > 1s gap\n","    has_gap = bool(window_samples[\"after_gap\"].any()) or \\\n","              (window_duration > WINDOW_SECONDS + 0.5)\n","\n","    # Build the row as a dict, starting with identity\n","    row = {\n","        \"subject_id\":      subject_id,\n","        \"source\":          source,\n","        \"window_start\":    window_start,\n","        \"window_end\":      window_end,\n","        \"window_duration\": window_duration,\n","        \"label\":           int(majority_label),\n","        \"activity\":        majority_activity,\n","        \"label_purity\":    round(label_purity, 4),\n","        \"has_gap\":         has_gap,\n","        \"n_samples\":       len(window_samples),\n","    }\n","\n","    # Add the 24 sensor features (4 stats × 6 axes)\n","    for col in ACCEL_COLS:\n","        row[f\"{col}_mean\"] = window_samples[col].mean()\n","        row[f\"{col}_std\"]  = window_samples[col].std()\n","        row[f\"{col}_min\"]  = window_samples[col].min()\n","        row[f\"{col}_max\"]  = window_samples[col].max()\n","\n","    return row\n","\n","print(\"summarize_window() defined\")"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"3VP_d9RwhiKM"},"source":["Defines the per-window summarization function. Each 2-second chunk of raw samples gets collapsed into a single row with identity info, a majority-vote label, a purity score, a gap flag, and 24 statistical features. Purity lets downstream code choose to exclude low-purity transition windows without losing them permanently, exactly the same flag-don't-drop principle used throughout the cleaning notebook."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":31,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"i5y8t0kxhjez","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070522997,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":158850,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}},"outputId":"e3b5d500-4b00-4269-818e-6da384171375"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["\n","Windowing subjects...\n","  HAR70+ 501: 103,860 samples → 1,029 windows\n","  HAR70+ 502: 131,367 samples → 1,301 windows\n","  HAR70+ 503: 116,413 samples → 1,155 windows\n","  HAR70+ 504: 150,758 samples → 1,495 windows\n","  HAR70+ 505: 87,006 samples → 861 windows\n","  HAR70+ 506: 122,714 samples → 1,209 windows\n","  HAR70+ 507: 120,125 samples → 1,188 windows\n","  HAR70+ 508: 130,494 samples → 1,291 windows\n","  HAR70+ 509: 121,763 samples → 1,201 windows\n","  HAR70+ 510: 122,061 samples → 1,208 windows\n","  HAR70+ 511: 128,063 samples → 1,272 windows\n","  HAR70+ 512: 119,310 samples → 1,182 windows\n","  HAR70+ 513: 123,599 samples → 1,218 windows\n","  HAR70+ 514: 101,510 samples → 998 windows\n","  HAR70+ 515: 153,517 samples → 1,519 windows\n","  HAR70+ 516: 138,278 samples → 1,367 windows\n","  HAR70+ 517: 147,045 samples → 1,453 windows\n","  HAR70+ 518: 141,714 samples → 1,408 windows\n","  HARTH S006: 204,355 samples → 2,012 windows\n","  HARTH S008: 418,989 samples → 4,155 windows\n","  HARTH S009: 154,464 samples → 1,538 windows\n","  HARTH S010: 351,649 samples → 3,505 windows\n","  HARTH S012: 382,414 samples → 3,792 windows\n","  HARTH S013: 369,077 samples → 3,641 windows\n","  HARTH S014: 366,487 samples → 3,605 windows\n","  HARTH S015: 418,392 samples → 4,150 windows\n","  HARTH S016: 355,418 samples → 3,523 windows\n","  HARTH S017: 366,609 samples → 3,634 windows\n","  HARTH S018: 322,271 samples → 3,188 windows\n","  HARTH S019: 297,945 samples → 2,954 windows\n","  HARTH S020: 371,496 samples → 3,684 windows\n","  HARTH S021: 302,247 samples → 2,988 windows\n","  HARTH S022: 337,602 samples → 3,320 windows\n","  HARTH S023: 137,646 samples → 1,372 windows\n","  HARTH S024: 170,534 samples → 1,695 windows\n","  HARTH S025: 231,729 samples → 2,301 windows\n","  HARTH S026: 195,172 samples → 1,946 windows\n","  HARTH S027: 158,584 samples → 1,573 windows\n","  HARTH S028: 165,178 samples → 1,644 windows\n","  HARTH S029: 178,716 samples → 1,780 windows\n","\n","Total windows: 84,355\n"]}],"source":["## D. Windowing execution\n","\n","# We window per subject to avoid creating windows that span subject boundaries.\n","# Within each subject, we group by 2-second time buckets using pandas' resample\n","# logic, which is fast and handles irregular timestamps gracefully.\n","\n","def window_subject(subject_df: pd.DataFrame) -> list:\n","    \"\"\"Split one subject's data into 2-second windows and summarize each.\"\"\"\n","\n","    # Sort by timestamp to ensure window ordering is correct\n","    subject_df = subject_df.sort_values(\"timestamp\").reset_index(drop=True)\n","\n","    # Floor each row's timestamp to the nearest 2-second boundary\n","    # All rows with the same floored timestamp belong to the same window\n","    window_key = subject_df[\"timestamp\"].dt.floor(f\"{WINDOW_SECONDS}s\")\n","\n","    rows = []\n","    # Group by the 2-second buckets\n","    for window_start, window_samples in subject_df.groupby(window_key):\n","        # Skip windows that are too sparse — indicates a big gap\n","        if len(window_samples) < MIN_SAMPLES_PER_WINDOW:\n","            continue\n","        rows.append(summarize_window(window_samples))\n","\n","    return rows\n","\n","# Process each subject separately — avoids creating cross-subject windows\n","print(\"\\nWindowing subjects...\")\n","all_rows = []\n","\n","for (subject_id, source), subject_df in df.groupby([\"subject_id\", \"source\"]):\n","    subject_rows = window_subject(subject_df)\n","    all_rows.extend(subject_rows)\n","    print(f\"  {source} {subject_id}: \"\n","          f\"{len(subject_df):,} samples → {len(subject_rows):,} windows\")\n","\n","# Combine all subject windows into the final fact table\n","windowed_df = pd.DataFrame(all_rows)\n","print(f\"\\nTotal windows: {len(windowed_df):,}\")"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"H1IeJ7E6hlwp"},"source":["Processes each subject independently. For each subject, samples are grouped into 2-second buckets using dt.floor(), and every bucket is summarized via summarize_window(). Windows with fewer than 95 samples (5% tolerance below the expected 100) are skipped — these indicate large gaps rather than a genuine window. Expected output: approximately 62k windows from HARTH and 22k from HAR70+, totaling ~85k."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":32,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"EpXtDwTihn1u","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070523051,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":40,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}},"outputId":"8ab09190-bb54-4e76-f047-63d7eb59c410"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Validating windowed output...\n","  ✓ Rule 1 (no nulls in identity/label columns)\n","  ✓ Rule 2 (label_purity in [0, 1])\n","  ✓ Rule 3 (window_duration in [1.88, 1.98]s)\n","  ✓ Rule 4 (activities in known codebook)\n","  ✓ Rule 5 (no nulls in feature columns)\n","\n","✓ All validation rules passed\n"]}],"source":["## E. Windowing validation — sanity checks on the output\n","\n","# Before saving, verify the windowed fact table satisfies expected invariants.\n","\n","print(\"Validating windowed output...\")\n","\n","# Rule 1: no nulls in identity or label columns\n","id_cols = [\"subject_id\", \"source\", \"window_start\", \"window_end\", \"activity\", \"label\"]\n","for c in id_cols:\n","    n_null = windowed_df[c].isnull().sum()\n","    assert n_null == 0, f\"  Rule 1 FAIL: {n_null} nulls in {c}\"\n","print(\"  ✓ Rule 1 (no nulls in identity/label columns)\")\n","\n","# Rule 2: label_purity in [0, 1]\n","assert windowed_df[\"label_purity\"].between(0, 1).all(), \\\n","    \"  Rule 2 FAIL: label_purity outside [0, 1]\"\n","print(\"  ✓ Rule 2 (label_purity in [0, 1])\")\n","\n","# Rule 3: window_duration reasonable — should be between 1.8s and ~3s\n","# (2s ideal, occasional longer if a gap is included)\n","min_dur = windowed_df[\"window_duration\"].min()\n","max_dur = windowed_df[\"window_duration\"].max()\n","assert min_dur >= 1.8, f\"  Rule 3 FAIL: window duration min={min_dur:.2f}s (too short)\"\n","print(f\"  ✓ Rule 3 (window_duration in [{min_dur:.2f}, {max_dur:.2f}]s)\")\n","\n","# Rule 4: activity values come from the known codebook\n","known_activities = {\n","    \"walking\", \"running\", \"shuffling\", \"stairs_up\", \"stairs_down\",\n","    \"standing\", \"sitting\", \"lying\", \"cycling_sit\", \"cycling_stand\",\n","    \"cycling_sit_inactive\", \"cycling_stand_inactive\",\n","}\n","unknown = set(windowed_df[\"activity\"].unique()) - known_activities\n","assert not unknown, f\"  Rule 4 FAIL: unknown activities {unknown}\"\n","print(\"  ✓ Rule 4 (activities in known codebook)\")\n","\n","# Rule 5: no accidental feature nulls\n","feature_cols = [f\"{col}_{fn}\" for col in ACCEL_COLS for fn in FEATURE_FUNCS]\n","n_feature_nulls = windowed_df[feature_cols].isnull().sum().sum()\n","assert n_feature_nulls == 0, f\"  Rule 5 FAIL: {n_feature_nulls} nulls in feature columns\"\n","print(\"  ✓ Rule 5 (no nulls in feature columns)\")\n","\n","print(\"\\n✓ All validation rules passed\")"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"jeJnTKqThqY_"},"source":["Five invariants the windowed output must satisfy: no nulls in identity or label columns, purity in valid range, window durations reasonable (at least 1.8s), activities from the known codebook, and no accidental nulls in the 24 feature columns. Any violation raises AssertionError, halting the notebook. This is the same fail-fast pattern used throughout the pipeline."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":33,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"tuKBmhbUhr0I","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070523077,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":12,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}},"outputId":"ea6b4838-0f32-4c71-fa0d-2a8b752256a7"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["=== Windowed dataset summary ===\n","\n","Total windows:          84,355\n","Windows per source:     \n","source\n","HARTH     62000\n","HAR70+    22355\n","\n","Windows per activity (all cohorts):\n","  sitting                     32,416  (38.4%)\n","  walking                     22,564  (26.7%)\n","  standing                    11,246  (13.3%)\n","  lying                        6,151  (7.3%)\n","  cycling_sit               