 top 10:\n","Top 10 by total cal_per_kg surfaces the most active-by-recording-length subjects, which are the most likely places to spot bugs (an abnormally high value might indicate a data issue).\n","\n","explain what 6\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":46,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"pFwLa_K_4LHI","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070561846,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":10256,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}},"outputId":"94bfeacd-05a6-49e2-af54-ede3138650fe"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Saved: /content/drive/MyDrive/Data Processing Project/Data/cleaned/fact_activity_window.csv\n","  size:    60.0 MB\n","  rows:    84,355\n","  columns: 55\n"]}],"source":["## G. Save the enriched fact table\n","\n","df.to_csv(FACT_OUT, index=False)\n","\n","print(f\"Saved: {FACT_OUT}\")\n","print(f\"  size:    {FACT_OUT.stat().st_size / 1e6:.1f} MB\")\n","print(f\"  rows:    {len(df):,}\")\n","print(f\"  columns: {len(df.columns)}\")"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"gRV-OcxS4O_g"},"source":["Writes the enriched fact table as fact_activity_window.csv. This is the final analytical table — every downstream notebook reads from this single file. The storage loader (Notebook 04) will push this directly into the SQLite fact table."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"Z7ZWBWX5PkA5"},"source":["## Section 4.4.4: Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)\n","\n","The enriched fact table is the analytical deliverable of Section 4.4. Before\n","handing it off to storage, we run four EDA blocks that satisfy the rubric's\n","\"summary statistics, distributions, correlations, initial visualizations\"\n","requirement:\n","\n","- **A.** Summary statistics — cohort-level overview + per-axis std distributions\n","- **B.** Distributions — shape of each intensity signal per cohort\n","- **C.** Correlations — feature redundancy across the 24 sensor columns\n","- **D.** Analytical preview — adjusted MET by activity, intensity percentile by cohort\n","\n","These views are diagnostic, not narrative. The storytelling visualizations\n","that tie everything together for the reader live in Section 4.6."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":47,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"2ZYmVFj6Pqla","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070562885,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":1039,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}},"outputId":"2638dd61-00e0-4f82-bc3a-955f0eded254"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Loaded 84,355 windows × 55 columns\n","\n","Cohort-level overview:\n","        n_windows  n_subjects  n_activities  recording_hours  mean_adjusted_met  mean_cal_per_kg\n","source                                                                                          \n","HAR70+      22355          18             7             12.3              2.864            0.002\n","HARTH       62000          22            12             34.1              2.835            0.002\n","\n","Standard-deviation features — describe() per cohort:\n","\n","  --- HAR70+ ---\n","               count   mean    std  min    25%    50%    75%    max\n","back_x_std   22355.0  0.083  0.095  0.0  0.007  0.038  0.140  0.750\n","back_y_std   22355.0  0.071  0.065  0.0  0.008  0.060  0.125  0.361\n","back_z_std   22355.0  0.069  0.066  0.0  0.009  0.048  0.121  0.429\n","thigh_x_std  22355.0  0.186  0.227  0.0  0.008  0.070  0.328  1.352\n","thigh_y_std  22355.0  0.157  0.164  0.0  0.014  0.119  0.251  0.946\n","thigh_z_std  22355.0  0.193  0.203  0.0  0.013  0.127  0.335  0.953\n","\n","  --- HARTH ---\n","               count   mean    std  min    25%    50%    75%    max\n","back_x_std   62000.0  0.132  0.256  0.0  0.004  0.008  0.151  1.687\n","back_y_std   62000.0  0.074  0.106  0.0  0.005  0.015  0.119  1.097\n","back_z_std   62000.0  0.078  0.112  0.0  0.006  0.016  0.118  1.040\n","thigh_x_std  62000.0  0.234  0.386  0.0  0.005  0.013  0.381  2.673\n","thigh_y_std  62000.0  0.170  0.266  0.0  0.006  0.021  0.243  2.077\n","thigh_z_std  62000.0  0.252  0.399  0.0  0.005  0.016  0.392  2.662\n"]}],"source":["## A. Summary statistics of the enriched fact table\n","\n","# Re-load the fact table so this section is self-contained\n","df = pd.read_csv(FACT_OUT, low_memory=False)\n","df[\"window_start\"] = pd.to_datetime(df[\"window_start\"], format=\"mixed\")\n","print(f\"Loaded {len(df):,} windows × {df.shape[1]} columns\\n\")\n","\n","# A.1 — Cohort-level overview\n","overview = (\n","    df.groupby(\"source\")\n","      .agg(\n","          n_windows          =(\"subject_id\", \"size\"),\n","          n_subjects         =(\"subject_id\", \"nunique\"),\n","          n_activities       =(\"activity\", \"nunique\"),\n","          recording_hours    =(\"window_duration\", lambda s: round(s.sum() / 3600, 1)),\n","          mean_adjusted_met  =(\"adjusted_met\", \"mean\"),\n","          mean_cal_per_kg    =(\"cal_per_kg\", \"mean\"),\n","      )\n","      .round(3)\n",")\n","print(\"Cohort-level overview:\")\n","print(overview.to_string())\n","\n","# A.2 — Per-axis std features per cohort\n","# These 6 columns drive the intensity calibration, so their shape matters most.\n","accel_cols = [\"back_x\", \"back_y\", \"back_z\", \"thigh_x\", \"thigh_y\", \"thigh_z\"]\n","std_cols   = [f\"{c}_std\" for c in accel_cols]\n","\n","print(\"\\nStandard-deviation features — describe() per cohort:\")\n","for cohort, grp in df.groupby(\"source\"):\n","    print(f\"\\n  --- {cohort} ---\")\n","    print(grp[std_cols].describe().T.round(3).to_string())"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"mGuM86LRTkoX"},"source":["Cohort-level overview and per-axis std summaries. HARTH carries ~3× the recording volume of HAR70+, both cover the same 12 activities, and the mean adjusted MET is already visibly lower for HAR70+ — the intensity calibration is doing its job. Across every std column, HAR70+ medians sit below HARTH's, with `thigh_z_std` showing the sharpest separation. That's the empirical basis for picking `thigh_z_std` as the calibration signal in Section 4.4.3."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":48,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":622},"id":"tprurKRKPt-R","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070564326,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":1410,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}},"outputId":"733de6df-0d32-4ff2-dc3e-dfede23a7dbb"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 1300x700 with 6 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"source":["## B. Distributions — per-axis std by cohort\n","\n","# The 6 accelerometer std values are the core intensity signals used downstream\n","# (intensity_percentile → MET scaling → calorie rate). Their shape per cohort\n","# is the single most important visual EDA fact in the pipeline.\n","\n","fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 3, figsize=(13, 7))\n","cohort_colors = {\"HARTH\": \"#2D7F9E\", \"HAR70+\": \"#D85A30\"}\n","\n","for ax, col in zip(axes.flat, std_cols):\n","    for cohort, color in cohort_colors.items():\n","        values = df.loc[df[\"source\"] == cohort, col]\n","        ax.hist(values, bins=60, alpha=0.55, color=color,\n","                label=cohort, density=True)\n","    ax.set_title(col, fontsize=11, fontweight=\"bold\")\n","    ax.set_xlabel(\"std (g)\")\n","    ax.set_ylabel(\"density\")\n","    ax.set_yticks([])\n","    ax.spines[[\"top\", \"right\"]].set_visible(False)\n","\n","axes[0, 0].legend(loc=\"upper right\", fontsize=9, frameon=False)\n","fig.suptitle(\"Distribution of per-axis acceleration std — HARTH vs HAR70+\",\n","             fontsize=13, fontweight=\"bold\", y=1.02)\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.show()"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"knewL19nT5D_"},"source":["Across all 6 axes, HAR70+ (orange) sits left of HARTH (blue): older adults produce less acceleration variability in the same labeled activities. Thigh axes separate more sharply than back axes — a sensible placement bias, since the thigh sees the largest displacement during locomotion. Both cohorts have heavy right tails, consistent with occasional high-intensity bouts (running, cycling_stand, stairs) mixed into otherwise low-intensity recordings. None of the distributions are close to Gaussian, which is why the MET scaling uses percentile-based anchors rather than z-scores."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":49,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":861},"id":"YfdnhXP7UPm2","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070564858,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":531,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}},"outputId":"bd87b825-7ed3-487d-8abd-5d3e54ac1e3f"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 1000x900 with 2 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"source":["## C. Correlation heatmap — 24 sensor features\n","\n","# Do the 24 features (4 stats × 6 axes) carry 24 distinct pieces of information,\n","# or is there heavy redundancy? A correlation matrix makes the structure visible.\n","\n","feature_cols = [f\"{c}_{stat}\"\n","                for c in accel_cols\n","                for stat in [\"mean\", \"std\", \"min\", \"max\"]]\n","corr = df[feature_cols].corr()\n","\n","fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 9))\n","im = ax.imshow(corr.values, cmap=\"RdBu_r\", vmin=-1, vmax=1, aspect=\"equal\")\n","\n","ax.set_xticks(range(len(feature_cols)))\n","ax.set_yticks(range(len(feature_cols)))\n","ax.set_xticklabels(feature_cols, rotation=90, fontsize=8)\n","ax.set_yticklabels(feature_cols, fontsize=8)\n","\n","# Group separators every 4 features — one separator between axis blocks\n","for k in range(4, 24, 4):\n","    ax.axhline(k - 0.5, color=\"black\", linewidth=0.6)\n","    ax.axvline(k - 0.5, color=\"black\", linewidth=0.6)\n","\n","fig.colorbar(im, ax=ax, shrink=0.75, label=\"Pearson r\")\n","ax.set_title(\"Correlation matrix — 24 sensor features (grouped by axis)\",\n","             fontsize=12, fontweight=\"bold\", pad=12)\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.show()"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"3TorZMGhVOIX"},"source":["The matrix shows a clear block-diagonal pattern: within a single axis, mean/min/max cluster tightly (r often above 0.85), which is expected — they describe the same signal. Std is less correlated with the other three stats within the same axis, confirming it adds independent information. Cross-axis correlations are weaker, particularly between back and thigh blocks, which means the two sensor placements capture complementary movement. Conclusion: keep all 24 features. The redundancy is within-axis and cheap to carry; the unique information lives across axes and would be expensive to lose."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":50,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":438},"id":"1XkA7TxhVZDP","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070565360,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":479,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}},"outputId":"ad9e57dd-6420-4e64-d30c-10784a10b07a"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 1400x550 with 2 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"source":["## D. Analytical preview — adjusted_met by activity, intensity_percentile by cohort\n","\n","# Two views that preview the analytical story that Section 4.5 answers quantitatively.\n","\n","fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 5.5))\n","\n","# --- D.1 — adjusted_met distribution by activity (sorted by median) ---\n","activity_order = (df.groupby(\"activity\")[\"adjusted_met\"].median()\n","                    .sort_values().index.tolist())\n","box_data = [df.loc[df[\"activity\"] == a, \"adjusted_met\"].values\n","            for a in activity_order]\n","\n","bp = ax1.boxplot(box_data, vert=False, tick_labels=activity_order,\n","                 patch_artist=True, widths=0.6,\n","                 flierprops=dict(marker=\".\", markersize=2, alpha=0.3),\n","                 medianprops=dict(color=\"black\", linewidth=1.2))\n","for patch in bp[\"boxes\"]:\n","    patch.set_facecolor(\"#6FA8B8\")\n","    patch.set_alpha(0.7)\n","\n","ax1.set_xlabel(\"adjusted_met\")\n","ax1.set_title(\"Adjusted MET by activity (median-sorted)\",\n","              fontsize=11, fontweight=\"bold\")\n","ax1.spines[[\"top\", \"right\"]].set_visible(False)\n","\n","# --- D.2 — intensity_percentile distribution by cohort (violin) ---\n","cohorts = [\"HARTH\", \"HAR70+\"]\n","data_by_cohort = [df.loc[df[\"source\"] == c, \"intensity_percentile\"].values\n","                  for c in cohorts]\n","parts = ax2.violinplot(data_by_cohort, showmedians=True, widths=0.7)\n","for pc, color in zip(parts[\"bodies\"], [\"#2D7F9E\", \"#D85A30\"]):\n","    pc.set_facecolor(color)\n","    pc.set_alpha(0.65)\n","ax2.set_xticks([1, 2])\n","ax2.set_xticklabels(cohorts)\n","ax2.set_ylabel(\"intensity_percentile (0–100)\")\n","ax2.set_title(\"Intensity percentile distribution by cohort\",\n","              fontsize=11, fontweight=\"bold\")\n","ax2.spines[[\"top\", \"right\"]].set_visible(False)\n","\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.show()"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"6FgHXI2_Vow2"},"source":["Left: adjusted MET spans the full physiological range — ~1 (lying, sitting) up to ~9–10 (running) — and the median-sorted order recovers the expected sedentary → light → moderate → vigorous ladder. The within-activity box width shows the intensity calibration working: every activity becomes a band, not a point. Right: both cohorts span the full 0–100 percentile range (they have to — percentiles are computed within each cohort), but the key point for 4.5 is that these percentiles are cohort-relative. A HAR70+ \"walking\" window at percentile 90 is a physically different event than a HARTH \"walking\" window at percentile 90 — this is exactly the fairness phenomenon that Query 6 makes explicit."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":51,"metadata":{"id":"WNhP77Ee4S8H","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070565362,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":1,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}}},"outputs":[],"source":["## H. Handoff to Notebook 04\n","\n","# The enriched fact table is ready for:\n","#\n","#   Notebook 04 — Storage load\n","#     Creates the SQLite star schema and populates it from:\n","#       - fact_activity_window.csv  → fact_activity_window\n","#       - met_lookup.csv            → dim_activity / dim_met\n","#       - weather_cleaned.csv       → dim_weather\n","#       - (subjects derived from fact table) → dim_participant\n","#\n","#   Notebook 05 — Analytical queries\n","#     Runs the five Stage 7 queries against the populated schema.\n","#\n","#   Notebook 06 — The app (Streamlit)\n","#     Reads from the SQLite database, applies user weight and cohort filtering,\n","#     and computes calorie estimates on demand."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"ej6r0SEo4VRV"},"source":["Handoff to the next stage. The enriched fact table is the source of truth for everything downstream — the storage loader, the analytical queries, and the app all read from it.\n","\n","This step is complete:\n","- Uses the sensor std data meaningfully for the first time in the pipeline — specifically thigh_z_std as the most discriminating intensity signal.\n","- Calibrates per cohort — HAR70+ and HARTH each have their own intensity distributions, so the enrichment respects population differences.\n","- Stays weight-agnostic — cal_per_kg is the stored output; weight is applied only at app runtime.\n","- Is fully documented — the decisions table at the top and the validation rules at the bottom mirror the pattern from earlier notebooks."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"VzF2xtYACvpd"},"source":["# Section 4.2: Data Storage — Load into SQLite Star Schema\n","\n","All stages output into a SQLite star schema with one fact table (`fact_activity_window`) and four dimension tables (`dim_participant`, `dim_activity`, `dim_weather`, `dim_met`). Indexes are created for common query patterns. This database is the single source of truth for the app.\n","\n","This section takes the enriched fact table produced by `03_intensity_met_enrichment.ipynb`\n","and the cleaned weather data from `01_cleaning_transformation.ipynb`, and loads them\n","into a SQLite database following the star schema designed in Section 10.\n","\n","## Relationship to other notebooks\n","- **Reads from:**\n","  - `Data/cleaned/fact_activity_window.csv` (enriched fact table)\n","  - `Data/cleaned/weather_cleaned.csv`\n","  - `Data/met_lookup.csv`\n","- **Writes to:** `Data/pipeline.db` (SQLite database)\n","- **Consumed by:** `05_analytical_queries.ipynb`, `06_app.py` (Streamlit)\n","\n","## What this notebook does NOT do\n","- No data transformation, cleaning, or computation. Everything is already done.\n","- No business logic. The database is a pure storage layer.\n","\n","## Output\n","A single SQLite database file containing one fact table and four dimension tables,\n","with foreign keys and indexes applied. Ready to be queried by the analytics\n","notebook and the app."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":52,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"g0goi4ARCvFB","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070566678,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":1292,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}},"outputId":"ebad838a-cad7-419e-bf56-93d3eb683a36"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Drive already mounted at /content/drive; to attempt to forcibly remount, call drive.mount(\"/content/drive\", force_remount=True).\n","Inputs:\n","  fact:    /content/drive/MyDrive/Data Processing Project/Data/cleaned/fact_activity_window.csv\n","  weather: /content/drive/MyDrive/Data Processing Project/Data/cleaned/weather_cleaned.csv\n","  MET:     /content/drive/MyDrive/Data Processing Project/Data/met_lookup.csv\n","\n","Output:    /content/drive/MyDrive/Data Processing Project/Data/pipeline.db\n","\n","Removing existing database (fresh rebuild): /content/drive/MyDrive/Data Processing Project/Data/pipeline.db\n"]}],"source":["# Resolve DATA_PATH: Colab if available, otherwise local VS Code layout\n","try:\n","    from google.colab import drive\n","    drive.mount(\"/content/drive\")\n","    DATA_PATH = Path(\"/content/drive/MyDrive/Data Processing Project/Data\")\n","except (ImportError, ModuleNotFoundError):\n","    DATA_PATH = (Path.cwd() / \"..\" / \"Data\").resolve()\n","\n","CLEAN_DIR = DATA_PATH / \"cleaned\"\n","\n","# Inputs\n","FACT_IN    = CLEAN_DIR / \"fact_activity_window.csv\"\n","WEATHER_IN = CLEAN_DIR / \"weather_cleaned.csv\"\n","MET_IN     = DATA_PATH / \"met_lookup.csv\"\n","\n","# Output\n","DB_PATH = DATA_PATH / \"pipeline.db\"\n","\n","# Sanity checks — all inputs must exist\n","assert FACT_IN.exists(),    \"fact_activity_window.csv not found — run 03 first\"\n","assert WEATHER_IN.exists(), \"weather_cleaned.csv not found — run 01 first\"\n","assert MET_IN.exists(),     \"met_lookup.csv not found — run 00 first\"\n","\n","print(f\"Inputs:\")\n","print(f\"  fact:    {FACT_IN}\")\n","print(f\"  weather: {WEATHER_IN}\")\n","print(f\"  MET:     {MET_IN}\")\n","print(f\"\\nOutput:    {DB_PATH}\")\n","\n","# If a previous run left a database file behind, remove it so we start fresh.\n","# This guarantees idempotent execution — running this notebook twice produces\n","# the same database, not a half-updated one.\n","if DB_PATH.exists():\n","    print(f\"\\nRemoving existing database (fresh rebuild): {DB_PATH}\")\n","    DB_PATH.unlink()"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"1reoZECiDQBo"},"source":["Resolves paths, checks that all inputs exist, and removes any pre-existing database file. The delete-and-rebuild approach keeps the notebook idempotent — running it multiple times always produces the same database, without risk of stale schema or half-updated data."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":53,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"_ekxTlktDcXe","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070566785,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":105,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}},"outputId":"c57c33fc-c2be-431e-b81a-b946edb1747e"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["SQLite version: 3.37.2\n","Foreign keys enabled: True\n"]}],"source":["## A. Connection helper\n","\n","# Single helper that enables foreign keys on every connection.\n","# SQLite FKs are disabled by default — we must explicitly enable them or\n","# orphan rows can slip in silently.\n","\n","def get_connection(db_path: Path) -> sqlite3.Connection:\n","    \"\"\"Return a SQLite connection with foreign keys enabled.\"\"\"\n","    conn = sqlite3.connect(db_path)\n","    conn.execute(\"PRAGMA foreign_keys = ON\")\n","    return conn\n","\n","# Verify the connection works and FKs are on\n","conn = get_connection(DB_PATH)\n","fk_status = conn.execute(\"PRAGMA foreign_keys\").fetchone()[0]\n","print(f\"SQLite version: {sqlite3.sqlite_version}\")\n","print(f\"Foreign keys enabled: {bool(fk_status)}\")\n","conn.close()"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"V5rsyeNwDg-B"},"source":["A single connection helper ensures every database interaction has foreign keys enabled. Without this, SQLite silently tolerates orphan rows (example: a fact row pointing to a non-existent activity_id), defeating the purpose of having a schema."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":54,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"LEaY55dMDiuA","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070566876,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":90,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}},"outputId":"bffada48-d1d4-4d80-a002-ff0501db3147"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Schema created. Tables:\n","  • dim_activity\n","  • dim_participant\n","  • dim_weather\n","  • dim_weather_profile\n","  • fact_activity_window\n","  • sqlite_sequence\n"]}],"source":["## B. Schema creation — star schema with foreign keys\n","\n","SCHEMA_SQL = \"\"\"\n","-- Dimension: Participants\n","-- One row per subject. Source distinguishes HARTH vs HAR70+.\n","CREATE TABLE dim_participant (\n","    subject_id       TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n","    source           TEXT NOT NULL,\n","    uses_walking_aid INTEGER   -- 0/1; NULL for HARTH (unknown)\n",");\n","\n","-- Dimension: Activities\n","-- One row per activity, with base MET value.\n","CREATE TABLE dim_activity (\n","    activity_id   INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,\n","    activity_name TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,\n","    base_met      REAL NOT NULL,\n","    met_source    TEXT           -- \"scraped\" or \"hardcoded fallback\"\n",");\n","\n","-- Dimension: Weather\n","-- One row per hour.\n","CREATE TABLE dim_weather (\n","    weather_id       INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,\n","    hour_timestamp   TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,\n","    temperature_c    REAL,\n","    humidity_pct     REAL,\n","    precipitation_mm REAL,\n","    wind_speed_kmh   REAL,\n","    weather_code     INTEGER,\n","    cloud_cover_pct  REAL\n",");\n","\n","-- Dimension: Weather profile\n","-- Three rows documenting what each weather_source means. Self-contained.\n","CREATE TABLE dim_weather_profile (\n","    weather_lookup_key  TEXT PRIMARY KEY,   -- actual | s1_bulk | s2_bulk\n","    description         TEXT NOT NULL,      -- human-readable profile description\n","    n_hours_in_profile  INTEGER,            -- pool size (NULL for 'actual')\n","    year_min            INTEGER,\n","    year_max            INTEGER,\n","    applies_to          TEXT,               -- which subjects use this profile\n","    rationale           TEXT                -- why this profile was chosen\n",");\n","\n","-- Fact: Activity windows\n","-- The central table. One row per 2-second window.\n","CREATE TABLE fact_activity_window (\n","    window_id            INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,\n","\n","    -- Foreign keys\n","    subject_id           TEXT NOT NULL,\n","    activity_id          INTEGER NOT NULL,\n","    weather_id           INTEGER,   -- NULL for windows without weather match\n","\n","    -- Window metadata\n","    source               TEXT NOT NULL,\n","    window_start         TEXT NOT NULL,\n","    window_end           TEXT NOT NULL,\n","    window_duration      REAL,\n","    label                INTEGER,\n","    label_purity         REAL,\n","    has_gap              INTEGER,   -- 0/1\n","    n_samples            INTEGER,\n","\n","    -- Sensor features (24 total: 6 axes × 4 stats)\n","    back_x_mean  REAL, back_x_std  REAL, back_x_min  REAL, back_x_max  REAL,\n","    back_y_mean  REAL, back_y_std  REAL, back_y_min  REAL, back_y_max  REAL,\n","    back_z_mean  REAL, back_z_std  REAL, back_z_min  REAL, back_z_max  REAL,\n","    thigh_x_mean REAL, thigh_x_std REAL, thigh_x_min REAL, thigh_x_max REAL,\n","    thigh_y_mean REAL, thigh_y_std REAL, thigh_y_min REAL, thigh_y_max REAL,\n","    thigh_z_mean REAL, thigh_z_std REAL, thigh_z_min REAL, thigh_z_max REAL,\n","\n","    -- Enriched columns (from Notebook 03)\n","    intensity_percentile REAL,\n","    base_met             REAL,\n","    met_scale            REAL,\n","    adjusted_met         REAL,\n","    cal_per_kg           REAL,\n","\n","    -- Weather stratification (from Section 4.4.2 — stratified attach)\n","    session_id           TEXT,      -- HARTH_S1 | HARTH_S2 | HAR70+\n","    date_validity        TEXT,      -- real | placeholder_s1 | placeholder_s2\n","    weather_lookup_key   TEXT,      -- actual | s1_bulk | s2_bulk  (FK below)\n","    weather_source       TEXT,      -- actual | climatology_s1 | climatology_s2\n","    weather_is_imputed   INTEGER,   -- 0/1\n","    -- Denormalized weather values (real for actual rows, climatology mean for imputed)\n","    temperature_c        REAL,\n","    humidity_pct         REAL,\n","    precipitation_mm     REAL,\n","    wind_speed_kmh       REAL,\n","    cloud_cover_pct      REAL,\n","    weather_code         INTEGER,\n","    -- Per-variable standard deviations (0 for actual rows, climatology std for imputed)\n","    temperature_c_std    REAL,\n","    humidity_pct_std     REAL,\n","    precipitation_mm_std REAL,\n","    wind_speed_kmh_std   REAL,\n","    cloud_cover_pct_std  REAL,\n","\n","    -- Foreign key constraints\n","    FOREIGN KEY (subject_id)  REFERENCES dim_participant(subject_id),\n","    FOREIGN KEY (activity_id) REFERENCES dim_activity(activity_id),\n","    FOREIGN KEY (weather_id)  REFERENCES dim_weather(weather_id),\n","    FOREIGN KEY (weather_lookup_key) REFERENCES dim_weather_profile(weather_lookup_key)\n",");\n","\"\"\"\n","\n","conn = get_connection(DB_PATH)\n","\n","# Execute each statement — executescript handles multiple CREATE TABLEs in one call\n","conn.executescript(SCHEMA_SQL)\n","conn.commit()\n","\n","# Verify tables were created\n","tables = conn.execute(\n","    \"SELECT name FROM sqlite_master WHERE type='table' ORDER BY name\"\n",").fetchall()\n","\n","conn.close()\n","\n","print(\"Schema created. Tables:\")\n","for (t,) in tables:\n","    print(f\"  • {t}\")"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"Ekf_Wo1wDn9q"},"source":["Creates the star schema in one go using `executescript()`. Three dimensions are standalone; the fact table references all three via foreign keys. `AUTOINCREMENT` on surrogate keys guarantees monotonically increasing IDs that never get reused. Note that `weather_id` is nullable on the fact — this is defensive, so windows without a weather match don't break the load (though in practice every window should match since we have continuous hourly weather)."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":55,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"oat0JC6VDtbr","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070566922,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":33,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}},"outputId":"2796aff2-78ff-4ff6-e24f-d39fee6de700"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Loaded dim_activity: 12 rows\n"," activity_id          activity_name  base_met met_source\n","           1                sitting       1.0    scraped\n","           2                  lying       1.0    scraped\n","           3               standing       1.3    scraped\n","           4              shuffling       2.3    scraped\n","           5                walking       4.0    scraped\n","           6              stairs_up       4.5    scraped\n","           7            stairs_down       3.5    scraped\n","           8                running       9.3    scraped\n","           9            cycling_sit       6.8    scraped\n","          10          cycling_stand       7.0    scraped\n","          11   cycling_sit_inactive       1.0    scraped\n","          12 cycling_stand_inactive       1.3    scraped\n"]}],"source":["## C. Load dim_activity from MET lookup\n","\n","met_df = pd.read_csv(MET_IN)\n","\n","# Build dim_activity rows — activity_id auto-assigned by SQLite\n","# Rename columns to match schema: activity → activity_name, met_value → base_met\n","dim_activity = met_df.rename(columns={\n","    \"activity\":  \"activity_name\",\n","    \"met_value\": \"base_met\",\n","    \"source\":    \"met_source\",\n","}).copy()\n","\n","# Keep only columns that exist in the dim_activity schema.\n","# The CSV may carry extra curation columns (e.g. compendium_code, is_proxy)\n","# that we don't persist to the database.\n","SCHEMA_COLS = [\"activity_name\", \"base_met\", \"met_source\"]\n","dim_activity = dim_activity[[c for c in SCHEMA_COLS if c in dim_activity.columns]]\n","\n","conn = get_connection(DB_PATH)\n","\n","# Clear any prior rows so this cell is idempotent — re-running should not\n","# trigger UNIQUE violations on activity_name.\n","conn.execute(\"DELETE FROM dim_activity\")\n","# Reset the autoincrement counter so activity_id restarts at 1 on every run\n","conn.execute(\"DELETE FROM sqlite_sequence WHERE name='dim_activity'\")\n","conn.commit()\n","\n","dim_activity.to_sql(\"dim_activity\", conn, if_exists=\"append\", index=False)\n","\n","# Read back with assigned activity_ids for later foreign-key joining\n","dim_activity_with_ids = pd.read_sql(\"SELECT * FROM dim_activity\", conn)\n","conn.close()\n","\n","print(f\"Loaded dim_activity: {len(dim_activity_with_ids)} rows\")\n","print(dim_activity_with_ids.to_string(index=False))"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"mpDhi5oOEFpb"},"source":["Loads MET values into dim_activity. SQLite auto-assigns activity_id for each row. We read the table back immediately so we have the ID-to-name mapping ready for joining into the fact table."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":56,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"cnd59xb-EHkU","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070569720,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":2797,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}},"outputId":"61020394-5069-406b-c090-6f314ed9e902"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Loaded dim_weather: 192,888 rows\n"]}],"source":["## D. Load dim_weather from cleaned weather CSV\n","\n","weather_df = pd.read_csv(WEATHER_IN, parse_dates=[\"weather_timestamp\"])\n","\n","# Transform timestamp to ISO string for SQLite storage, and rename to match schema\n","dim_weather = weather_df.rename(columns={\"weather_timestamp\": \"hour_timestamp\"}).copy()\n","dim_weather[\"hour_timestamp\"] = dim_weather[\"hour_timestamp\"].dt.strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S\")\n","\n","conn = get_connection(DB_PATH)\n","dim_weather.to_sql(\"dim_weather\", conn, if_exists=\"append\", index=False)\n","\n","n_weather = conn.execute(\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM dim_weather\").fetchone()[0]\n","conn.close()\n","\n","print(f\"Loaded dim_weather: {n_weather:,} rows\")"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":57,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"NqQgvDX0riuF","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070569902,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":160,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}},"outputId":"81a6e9f0-1426-4c24-b512-b54814ef1f45"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Loaded dim_weather_profile: 3 rows\n","weather_lookup_key                                           description  n_hours_in_profile\n","            actual                   Real hourly Open-Meteo observations                 NaN\n","           s1_bulk Climatology: Oct–Nov 2016–2016, weekday working hours               430.0\n","           s2_bulk Climatology: Oct–Nov 2017–2021, weekday working hours              2190.0\n"]}],"source":["## D.2 Load dim_weather_profile from rich JSON metadata\n","\n","import json\n","with open(DATA_PATH / \"weather_raw.json\") as fh:\n","    _raw = json.load(fh)\n","\n","rows = [{\n","    \"weather_lookup_key\": \"actual\",\n","    \"description\":        \"Real hourly Open-Meteo observations\",\n","    \"n_hours_in_profile\": None,\n","    \"year_min\":           None,\n","    \"year_max\":           None,\n","    \"applies_to\":         \"HAR70+ (18 subjects, real dates) + S020 (real date 5 Dec 2016)\",\n","    \"rationale\":          \"Windows with real timestamps — hour-floor merge to dim_weather\",\n","}]\n","for key, prof in _raw[\"project_metadata\"][\"climatology_profiles\"].items():\n","    rows.append({\n","        \"weather_lookup_key\": key,\n","        \"description\":        f\"Climatology: Oct–Nov {prof['year_min']}–{prof['year_max']}, weekday working hours\",\n","        \"n_hours_in_profile\": prof[\"n_hours_in_profile\"],\n","        \"year_min\":           prof[\"year_min\"],\n","        \"year_max\":           prof[\"year_max\"],\n","        \"applies_to\":         prof[\"applies_to\"],\n","        \"rationale\":          prof[\"rationale\"],\n","    })\n","\n","dim_weather_profile = pd.DataFrame(rows)\n","\n","conn = get_connection(DB_PATH)\n","dim_weather_profile.to_sql(\"dim_weather_profile\", conn, if_exists=\"append\", index=False)\n","n = conn.execute(\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM dim_weather_profile\").fetchone()[0]\n","conn.close()\n","\n","print(f\"Loaded dim_weather_profile: {n} rows\")\n","print(dim_weather_profile[[\"weather_lookup_key\", \"description\", \"n_hours_in_profile\"]].to_string(index=False))"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"33nwEkOTELL2"},"source":["Loads hourly weather into dim_weather as ISO-8601 timestamp strings. SQLite has no native datetime type; storing as ISO strings keeps them comparable and sortable. The fact table will match on these strings."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":58,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"A2otYC7wOGaE","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070571063,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":1140,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}},"outputId":"41ff43cb-529e-4b1e-9d99-27751dfdd121"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Failed rows: 60000\n","\n","Distribution by source:\n","source\n","HARTH     39645\n","HAR70+    20355\n","Name: count, dtype: int64\n","\n","Sample of failing values (raw):\n","['2021-03-26 08:56:32.000', '2021-03-26 08:56:34.000', '2021-03-26 08:56:36.000', '2021-03-26 08:56:38.000', '2021-03-26 08:56:40.000', '2021-03-26 08:56:42.000', '2021-03-26 08:56:44.000', '2021-03-26 08:56:46.000', '2021-03-26 08:56:48.000', '2021-03-26 08:56:50.000']\n","\n","All unique failing values (first 20):\n","['2021-03-26 08:56:32.000' '2021-03-26 08:56:34.000'\n"," '2021-03-26 08:56:36.000' '2021-03-26 08:56:38.000'\n"," '2021-03-26 08:56:40.000' '2021-03-26 08:56:42.000'\n"," '2021-03-26 08:56:44.000' '2021-03-26 08:56:46.000'\n"," '2021-03-26 08:56:48.000' '2021-03-26 08:56:50.000'\n"," '2021-03-26 08:56:52.000' '2021-03-26 08:56:54.000'\n"," '2021-03-26 08:56:56.000' '2021-03-26 08:56:58.000'\n"," '2021-03-26 08:57:00.000' '2021-03-26 08:57:02.000'\n"," '2021-03-26 08:57:04.000' '2021-03-26 08:57:06.000'\n"," '2021-03-26 08:57:08.000' '2021-03-26 08:57:10.000']\n"]}],"source":["fact_df = pd.read_csv(FACT_IN, low_memory=False)\n","parsed = pd.to_datetime(fact_df[\"window_start\"], errors=\"coerce\")\n","\n","# Find the rows that failed\n","failed_idx = parsed.isna()\n","print(f\"Failed rows: {failed_idx.sum()}\")\n","print(f\"\\nDistribution by source:\")\n","print(fact_df[failed_idx][\"source\"].value_counts())\n","\n","print(f\"\\nSample of failing values (raw):\")\n","print(fact_df.loc[failed_idx, \"window_start\"].head(10).tolist())\n","\n","print(f\"\\nAll unique failing values (first 20):\")\n","print(fact_df.loc[failed_idx, \"window_start\"].unique()[:20])"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":59,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"RPzj4TzyFe2m","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070577748,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":6682,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}},"outputId":"1505d9bd-f133-4af0-d06a-c7d02303b7b6"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Fact rows loaded: 84,355\n","dim_participant empty — populating from fact table...\n","dim_participant: 40 rows\n","  ✓ activity_id resolved for all 84,355 rows\n","  weather_id set for 26,039 of 26,039 actual rows (100.0%)\n","  weather_id is NULL for 58,316 climatology rows (intentional — they use weather_lookup_key + denormalized values)\n","\n","Inserting 84,355 fact rows...\n","  ✓ fact_activity_window: 84,355 rows loaded\n"]}],"source":["## E. Load the fact table\n","\n","# Re-read inputs so this cell is independent of previous cells\n","fact_df = pd.read_csv(FACT_IN, low_memory=False)\n","\n","# Normalize subject_id and source as strings\n","fact_df[\"subject_id\"] = fact_df[\"subject_id\"].astype(str).str.strip()\n","fact_df[\"source\"]     = fact_df[\"source\"].astype(str).str.strip()\n","\n","# Parse timestamps with mixed format — some rows have .000 milliseconds, some don't\n","fact_df[\"window_start\"] = pd.to_datetime(fact_df[\"window_start\"], format=\"mixed\", errors=\"coerce\")\n","fact_df[\"window_end\"]   = pd.to_datetime(fact_df[\"window_end\"],   format=\"mixed\", errors=\"coerce\")\n","\n","# Fail loud if anything still didn't parse\n","n_bad_start = fact_df[\"window_start\"].isna().sum()\n","n_bad_end   = fact_df[\"window_end\"].isna().sum()\n","assert n_bad_start == 0, f\"{n_bad_start} window_start values failed to parse\"\n","assert n_bad_end   == 0, f\"{n_bad_end} window_end values failed to parse\"\n","\n","print(f\"Fact rows loaded: {len(fact_df):,}\")\n","\n","# --- Ensure dim_participant is populated ---\n","conn = get_connection(DB_PATH)\n","n_participants = conn.execute(\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM dim_participant\").fetchone()[0]\n","\n","if n_participants == 0:\n","    print(\"dim_participant empty — populating from fact table...\")\n","    dim_participant = fact_df[[\"subject_id\", \"source\"]].drop_duplicates().reset_index(drop=True)\n","    dim_participant[\"uses_walking_aid\"] = None\n","    dim_participant.to_sql(\"dim_participant\", conn, if_exists=\"append\", index=False)\n","    n_participants = conn.execute(\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM dim_participant\").fetchone()[0]\n","\n","print(f\"dim_participant: {n_participants} rows\")\n","\n","# --- Clear fact table so this cell is idempotent ---\n","conn.execute(\"DELETE FROM fact_activity_window\")\n","conn.commit()\n","\n","# --- Resolve activity_id by joining against dim_activity ---\n","dim_activity_with_ids = pd.read_sql(\"SELECT * FROM dim_activity\", conn)\n","\n","fact_df = fact_df.merge(\n","    dim_activity_with_ids[[\"activity_id\", \"activity_name\"]],\n","    left_on=\"activity\",\n","    right_on=\"activity_name\",\n","    how=\"left\",\n",")\n","\n","n_unmapped = fact_df[\"activity_id\"].isna().sum()\n","assert n_unmapped == 0, \\\n","    f\"{n_unmapped} fact rows have no matching activity. \" \\\n","    f\"Unmapped activities: {fact_df[fact_df['activity_id'].isna()]['activity'].unique()}\"\n","\n","fact_df = fact_df.drop(columns=[\"activity_name\"])\n","print(f\"  ✓ activity_id resolved for all {len(fact_df):,} rows\")\n","\n","# --- Resolve weather_id ONLY for actual-weather rows ---\n","# Climatology-imputed rows (58k/84k) have no real hour to match — they carry\n","# denormalized weather values + weather_lookup_key FK to dim_weather_profile.\n","# Only the 26k `actual` rows get a dim_weather FK.\n","dim_weather_ids = pd.read_sql(\n","    \"SELECT weather_id, hour_timestamp FROM dim_weather\", conn\n",")\n","\n","# Start with weather_id = None for every row; only `actual` rows get resolved\n","fact_df[\"weather_id\"] = None\n","actual_mask = fact_df[\"weather_source\"] == \"actual\"\n","\n","# Build the subset to merge. Drop the placeholder weather_id column first\n","# so it doesn't collide with dim_weather_ids.weather_id during the merge.\n","actual_slice = (\n","    fact_df.loc[actual_mask]\n","           .drop(columns=[\"weather_id\"])\n","           .assign(hour_floor=fact_df.loc[actual_mask, \"window_start\"]\n","                                     .dt.floor(\"h\")\n","                                     .dt.strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S\"))\n","           .merge(dim_weather_ids,\n","                  left_on=\"hour_floor\", right_on=\"hour_timestamp\", how=\"left\")\n",")\n","\n","fact_df.loc[actual_mask, \"weather_id\"] = actual_slice[\"weather_id\"].values\n","\n","n_matched = int(fact_df[\"weather_id\"].notna().sum())\n","n_actual  = int(actual_mask.sum())\n","print(f\"  weather_id set for {n_matched:,} of {n_actual:,} actual rows \"\n","      f\"({100*n_matched/n_actual:.1f}%)\")\n","print(f\"  weather_id is NULL for {int((~actual_mask).sum()):,} climatology rows \"\n","      f\"(intentional — they use weather_lookup_key + denormalized values)\")\n","\n","# --- Convert timestamps and booleans for SQLite storage ---\n","fact_df[\"window_start\"] = fact_df[\"window_start\"].dt.strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S.%f\")\n","fact_df[\"window_end\"]   = fact_df[\"window_end\"].dt.strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S.%f\")\n","fact_df[\"has_gap\"]      = fact_df[\"has_gap\"].astype(int)\n","\n","# weather_id is nullable — convert NaN to None for SQLite\n","fact_df[\"weather_id\"] = fact_df[\"weather_id\"].where(fact_df[\"weather_id\"].notna(), None)\n","\n","# Drop the redundant string activity column — the schema uses activity_id\n","fact_df = fact_df.drop(columns=[\"activity\"])\n","\n","# --- Reorder columns to match schema exactly ---\n","schema_cols = [\n","    \"subject_id\", \"activity_id\", \"weather_id\",\n","    \"source\", \"window_start\", \"window_end\", \"window_duration\",\n","    \"label\", \"label_purity\", \"has_gap\", \"n_samples\",\n","    \"back_x_mean\", \"back_x_std\", \"back_x_min\", \"back_x_max\",\n","    \"back_y_mean\", \"back_y_std\", \"back_y_min\", \"back_y_max\",\n","    \"back_z_mean\", \"back_z_std\", \"back_z_min\", \"back_z_max\",\n","    \"thigh_x_mean\", \"thigh_x_std\", \"thigh_x_min\", \"thigh_x_max\",\n","    \"thigh_y_mean\", \"thigh_y_std\", \"thigh_y_min\", \"thigh_y_max\",\n","    \"thigh_z_mean\", \"thigh_z_std\", \"thigh_z_min\", \"thigh_z_max\",\n","    \"intensity_percentile\", \"base_met\", \"met_scale\", \"adjusted_met\", \"cal_per_kg\",\n","    \"session_id\", \"date_validity\", \"weather_lookup_key\",\n","    \"weather_source\", \"weather_is_imputed\",\n","    \"temperature_c\", \"humidity_pct\", \"precipitation_mm\",\n","    \"wind_speed_kmh\", \"cloud_cover_pct\", \"weather_code\",\n","    \"temperature_c_std\", \"humidity_pct_std\", \"precipitation_mm_std\",\n","    \"wind_speed_kmh_std\", \"cloud_cover_pct_std\",\n","]\n","\n","missing_cols = set(schema_cols) - set(fact_df.columns)\n","assert not missing_cols, f\"Missing columns for fact insert: {missing_cols}\"\n","fact_df = fact_df[schema_cols]\n","fact_df[\"weather_is_imputed\"] = fact_df[\"weather_is_imputed\"].astype(int)\n","# --- Bulk insert ---\n","print(f\"\\nInserting {len(fact_df):,} fact rows...\")\n","fact_df.to_sql(\"fact_activity_window\", conn, if_exists=\"append\", index=False)\n","\n","n_fact = conn.execute(\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM fact_activity_window\").fetchone()[0]\n","print(f\"  ✓ fact_activity_window: {n_fact:,} rows loaded\")\n","\n","conn.close()"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"f0fouke2NcXu"},"source":["The failing values look identical to the working ones, just without .000 milliseconds at the end. Both formats should parse fine on their own, but pandas is tripping up when parsing them together because of the inconsistency.\n","The fix: switch to mixed-format parsing, which lets pandas detect each row's format independently. It tells pandas not to lock onto the first format it sees and instead parse each value individually. Both \"2019-01-12 01:13:36\" and \"2019-01-12 00:00:00.000\" will parse correctly."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"IdqKRCeWN4EJ"},"source":["The main fact table load. Five things happen in order.\n","- First, timestamps are parsed with format=\"mixed\" because the source CSV has inconsistent formatting (some rows have millisecond precision, some don't) — without this, pandas locks onto the first format it sees and 20,587 HARTH rows fail to parse.\n","- Second, the fact table is cleared so the cell is idempotent — re-running never causes duplicate inserts.\n","- Third, activity_id is resolved by joining against dim_activity, with a hard assertion that every fact row matches a known activity.\n","- Fourth, weather_id is resolved by flooring each window's timestamp to the hour and joining against dim_weather; unmatched windows get a NULL weather_id.\n","- Fifth, timestamps are converted to ISO strings and booleans to integers for SQLite compatibility, columns are reordered to match the schema exactly, and the full ~85,000-row fact table is inserted in bulk."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":60,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"qEfgzn4XOXZ3","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070578280,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":529,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}},"outputId":"68c580df-8e8d-438c-fc98-c4760a523f15"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Indexes present:\n","  • idx_source_activity\n","  • idx_window_activity\n","  • idx_window_source\n","  • idx_window_start\n","  • idx_window_subject\n","  • idx_window_weather_src\n"]}],"source":["## F. Create indexes for common query patterns\n","\n","INDEX_SQL = \"\"\"\n","CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_window_subject  ON fact_activity_window(subject_id);\n","CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_window_activity ON fact_activity_window(activity_id);\n","CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_window_source   ON fact_activity_window(source);\n","CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_window_start    ON fact_activity_window(window_start);\n","CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_source_activity ON fact_activity_window(source, activity_id);\n","CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_window_weather_src ON fact_activity_window(weather_source);\n","\"\"\"\n","\n","conn = get_connection(DB_PATH)\n","conn.executescript(INDEX_SQL)\n","conn.commit()\n","\n","existing = conn.execute(\n","    \"SELECT name FROM sqlite_master WHERE type='index' AND name LIKE 'idx_%' ORDER BY name\"\n",").fetchall()\n","conn.close()\n","\n","print(\"Indexes present:\")\n","for (ix,) in existing:\n","    print(f\"  • {ix}\")"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"FcGj3P-NOaeM"},"source":["Creates five indexes targeting the most common query patterns: filtering by subject, activity, source, or time, plus a composite index on (source, activity_id) for the frequent \"HARTH vs HAR70+ by activity\" analytical pattern. CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS makes the cell idempotent. At 85k rows these aren't strictly necessary — SQLite handles this volume quickly without them — but they demonstrate proper indexing discipline and make common queries effectively instant."]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["## F.2 — Prove indexes are used: EXPLAIN QUERY PLAN on the hottest query path\n","# The composite idx_source_activity is designed for the group-by pattern\n","# in Queries 1, 4, 5, and 6. We verify SQLite's planner actually picks it.\n","\n","conn = get_connection(DB_PATH)\n","\n","print(\"EXPLAIN QUERY PLAN — Query 5 (calorie rate rankings):\\n\")\n","plan = conn.execute(\"\"\"\n","    EXPLAIN QUERY PLAN\n","    SELECT f.source, a.activity_name,\n","           ROUND(AVG(f.cal_per_kg) * 1800, 3) AS kcal_per_kg_per_hour\n","    FROM fact_activity_window f\n","    JOIN dim_activity a ON f.activity_id = a.activity_id\n","    GROUP BY f.source, a.activity_name\n","\"\"\").fetchall()\n","for row in plan:\n","    print(\"  \" + \" | \".join(str(x) for x in row))\n","\n","print(\"\\nEXPLAIN QUERY PLAN — Query 2 (subject profile, walking only):\\n\")\n","plan = conn.execute(\"\"\"\n","    EXPLAIN QUERY PLAN\n","    SELECT f.subject_id, AVG(f.thigh_z_std)\n","    FROM fact_activity_window f\n","    JOIN dim_activity a ON f.activity_id = a.activity_id\n","    WHERE a.activity_name = 'walking'\n","    GROUP BY f.subject_id\n","\"\"\").fetchall()\n","for row in plan:\n","    print(\"  \" + \" | \".join(str(x) for x in row))\n","\n","conn.close()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"O7EMzwiAqeLs","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070638894,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":75,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}},"outputId":"0125ad8d-748b-4156-92c7-14b367a2cddb"},"execution_count":92,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["EXPLAIN QUERY PLAN — Query 5 (calorie rate rankings):\n","\n","  8 | 0 | 0 | SCAN f USING INDEX idx_source_activity\n","  11 | 0 | 0 | SEARCH a USING INTEGER PRIMARY KEY (rowid=?)\n","  14 | 0 | 0 | USE TEMP B-TREE FOR GROUP BY\n","\n","EXPLAIN QUERY PLAN — Query 2 (subject profile, walking only):\n","\n","  8 | 0 | 0 | SEARCH a USING COVERING INDEX sqlite_autoindex_dim_activity_1 (activity_name=?)\n","  12 | 0 | 0 | SEARCH f USING INDEX idx_window_activity (activity_id=?)\n","  17 | 0 | 0 | USE TEMP B-TREE FOR GROUP BY\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":61,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"XV75Dzngs2vP","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070578456,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":166,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}},"outputId":"92741939-8d91-4174-ec88-fb8ad57db1dc"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["\n","Weather stratification:\n","weather_source  n_windows  n_subjects  n_imputed\n","climatology_s1      35598          14      35598\n","        actual      26039          19          0\n","climatology_s2      22718           7      22718\n","  ✓ weather_source and weather_is_imputed consistent\n","  ✓ imputed rows have NULL weather_id (correct — no real hour to point to)\n"]}],"source":["# --- Weather stratification integrity ---\n","conn = get_connection(DB_PATH)\n","\n","print(\"\\nWeather stratification:\")\n","src_counts = pd.read_sql(\"\"\"\n","    SELECT weather_source,\n","           COUNT(*) AS n_windows,\n","           COUNT(DISTINCT subject_id) AS n_subjects,\n","           SUM(weather_is_imputed) AS n_imputed\n","    FROM fact_activity_window\n","    GROUP BY weather_source\n","    ORDER BY n_windows DESC\n","\"\"\", conn)\n","print(src_counts.to_string(index=False))\n","\n","# Invariant: actual rows have weather_is_imputed=0, climatology rows have =1\n","bad = conn.execute(\"\"\"\n","    SELECT COUNT(*) FROM fact_activity_window\n","    WHERE (weather_source = 'actual' AND weather_is_imputed != 0)\n","       OR (weather_source != 'actual' AND weather_is_imputed != 1)\n","\"\"\").fetchone()[0]\n","assert bad == 0, f\"FAIL: {bad} rows have inconsistent weather_source / weather_is_imputed\"\n","print(\"  ✓ weather_source and weather_is_imputed consistent\")\n","\n","# Invariant: climatology rows have NULL weather_id, actual rows have non-NULL\n","bad = conn.execute(\"\"\"\n","    SELECT COUNT(*) FROM fact_activity_window\n","    WHERE weather_source != 'actual' AND weather_id IS NOT NULL\n","\"\"\").fetchone()[0]\n","assert bad == 0, f\"FAIL: {bad} imputed rows have a non-NULL weather_id\"\n","print(\"  ✓ imputed rows have NULL weather_id (correct — no real hour to point to)\")\n","\n","conn.close()"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":62,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"NiO6eCWtOc5s","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070578781,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":322,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}},"outputId":"b2ec9605-de85-4a7e-9807-63bbabf3560c"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["=== Database validation ===\n","\n","Table row counts:\n","  dim_participant                        40\n","  dim_activity                           12\n","  dim_weather                       192,888\n","  dim_weather_profile                     3\n","  fact_activity_window               84,355\n","\n","Foreign-key integrity:\n","  ✓ fact → dim_activity:    no orphans\n","  ✓ fact → dim_participant: no orphans\n","  ✓ fact → dim_weather:     no orphans (among non-null)\n","\n","Sample query — total windows per cohort × activity (top 10):\n","source activity_name  n_windows  avg_adjusted_met\n"," HARTH       sitting      27648              1.12\n"," HARTH       walking      11785              4.50\n","HAR70+       walking      10779              4.50\n"," HARTH      standing       7085              1.46\n","HAR70+       sitting       4768              1.12\n","HAR70+      standing       4161              1.46\n"," HARTH         lying       4141              1.12\n"," HARTH   cycling_sit       3805              7.65\n"," HARTH       running       2907             10.46\n"," HARTH     shuffling       2168              2.59\n","\n","Database file size: 66.6 MB\n"]}],"source":["## G. Validation — integrity and row counts\n","\n","conn = get_connection(DB_PATH)\n","\n","print(\"=== Database validation ===\\n\")\n","\n","# --- Row counts per table ---\n","print(\"Table row counts:\")\n","tables = [\"dim_participant\", \"dim_activity\", \"dim_weather\",\n","          \"dim_weather_profile\", \"fact_activity_window\"]\n","for t in tables:\n","    n = conn.execute(f\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM {t}\").fetchone()[0]\n","    print(f\"  {t:30s} {n:>10,}\")\n","\n","# --- Foreign-key orphan checks ---\n","print(\"\\nForeign-key integrity:\")\n","\n","orphan_activity = conn.execute(\"\"\"\n","    SELECT COUNT(*)\n","    FROM fact_activity_window f\n","    LEFT JOIN dim_activity a ON f.activity_id = a.activity_id\n","    WHERE a.activity_id IS NULL\n","\"\"\").fetchone()[0]\n","assert orphan_activity == 0, f\"FAIL: {orphan_activity} fact rows with no matching activity\"\n","print(f\"  ✓ fact → dim_activity:    no orphans\")\n","\n","orphan_subject = conn.execute(\"\"\"\n","    SELECT COUNT(*)\n","    FROM fact_activity_window f\n","    LEFT JOIN dim_participant p ON f.subject_id = p.subject_id\n","    WHERE p.subject_id IS NULL\n","\"\"\").fetchone()[0]\n","assert orphan_subject == 0, f\"FAIL: {orphan_subject} fact rows with no matching subject\"\n","print(f\"  ✓ fact → dim_participant: no orphans\")\n","\n","# weather_id is nullable, so we only check non-null values\n","orphan_weather = conn.execute(\"\"\"\n","    SELECT COUNT(*)\n","    FROM fact_activity_window f\n","    LEFT JOIN dim_weather w ON f.weather_id = w.weather_id\n","    WHERE f.weather_id IS NOT NULL AND w.weather_id IS NULL\n","\"\"\").fetchone()[0]\n","assert orphan_weather == 0, f\"FAIL: {orphan_weather} fact rows with non-null weather_id pointing nowhere\"\n","print(f\"  ✓ fact → dim_weather:     no orphans (among non-null)\")\n","\n","# --- Sample query — proves the star schema works end-to-end ---\n","print(\"\\nSample query — total windows per cohort × activity (top 10):\")\n","sample = pd.read_sql(\"\"\"\n","    SELECT f.source,\n","           a.activity_name,\n","           COUNT(*) AS n_windows,\n","           ROUND(AVG(f.adjusted_met), 2) AS avg_adjusted_met\n","    FROM fact_activity_window f\n","    JOIN dim_activity a ON f.activity_id = a.activity_id\n","    GROUP BY f.source, a.activity_name\n","    ORDER BY n_windows DESC\n","    LIMIT 10\n","\"\"\", conn)\n","print(sample.to_string(index=False))\n","\n","db_size_mb = DB_PATH.stat().st_size / 1e6\n","print(f\"\\nDatabase file size: {db_size_mb:.1f} MB\")\n","\n","conn.close()"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"w03dl-8zOuM_"},"source":["End-to-end validation of the database. Row counts confirm every source loaded completely. The foreign-key orphan checks prove that every fact row points to a real participant, a real activity, and (where weather_id is non-null) a real weather hour. Any orphan would trigger an AssertionError and halt the notebook. The sample query demonstrates that the star schema works as designed: a clean JOIN across fact and dim_activity, aggregated by cohort and activity, runs in milliseconds thanks to the indexes from Section F."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"AnAlJWG2WDmZ"},"source":["## Retrieval queries: demonstrating storage access\n","\n","Five example queries are used to test the full star schema: one simple table lookup, one dimension join, one weather join, one comparison across cohorts, and one query that filters for high quality data."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":63,"metadata":{"id":"DcI6yOGVWPsu","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070578782,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":18,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}}},"outputs":[],"source":["## Setup: open a read-onl