0,\n        \"min\": 1.0,\n        \"max\": 1.0,\n        \"num_unique_values\": 1,\n        \"samples\": [\n          1.0\n        ],\n        \"semantic_type\": \"\",\n        \"description\": \"\"\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}"}},"metadata":{},"execution_count":68}],"source":["## Query 5: High-quality windows only (filter on quality flags)\n","# Returns the first 20 windows that satisfy both quality conditions:\n","# label_purity ≥ 0.95 (clean single-activity window) AND has_gap = 0\n","# (no sensor gap crossed). Exercises the composite index on (subject_id,\n","# window_start) plus the quality-flag filter.\n","\n","pd.read_sql(\"\"\"\n","    SELECT subject_id,\n","           source,\n","           window_start,\n","           adjusted_met,\n","           label_purity\n","    FROM fact_activity_window\n","    WHERE label_purity >= 0.95\n","      AND has_gap = 0\n","    ORDER BY window_start\n","    LIMIT 20\n","\"\"\", conn)"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["All 20 returned windows have label purity of 1.0, and the query also filters for has_gap = 0. This means the output is limited to clean windows with a stable activity label and no detected sensor gap.\n","\n","Adjusted MET still ranges from 0.928 to 6.322, so the quality filter removes noisy segments without flattening real intensity differences. The repeated 2000-01-01 timestamp reflects HARTH's anonymized placeholder date, which is handled earlier through climatology-based weather mapping."],"metadata":{"id":"vlrq9MuhssD1"}},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":69,"metadata":{"id":"Ln2cdMGuYKj2","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070579028,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":7,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}}},"outputs":[],"source":["## Close the retrieval connection: Section 4.5 opens its own\n","\n","conn.close()"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":70,"metadata":{"id":"XIpEcnGYOxaK","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070579068,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":41,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}},"outputId":"24f371cb-0538-43e1-f062-e96e37f67130"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["✓ Storage load complete. Ready for Notebook 05.\n"]}],"source":["## H. Handoff to Notebook 05\n","\n","# The database is ready for:\n","#\n","#   Notebook 05 — Analytical SQL queries\n","#     Five queries covering cohort distributions, subject profiles,\n","#     intensity spread, calorie-rate rankings, and fairness checks.\n","#\n","#   Notebook 06 — The Streamlit app\n","#     Reads from pipeline.db at runtime to compute calorie estimates and\n","#     activity recommendations personalized by weight and cohort.\n","\n","print(\"✓ Storage load complete. Ready for Notebook 05.\")"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"pAyUvlTiOzjK"},"source":["Explicit handoff to the next stage. From this point on, no notebook reads from the cleaned CSVs directly, as they all query pipeline.db. The CSVs remain in place as the auditable, human-readable backup."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"WXmvS4nQP96X"},"source":["# Section 4.5: Analytical Queries & Insights\n","\n","This notebook runs six analytical SQL queries against the SQLite database\n","produced in Section 4.2. The queries answer the concrete business\n","and fairness questions the pipeline was designed to support.\n","\n","## Relationship to other notebooks\n","- **Reads from:** `Data/pipeline.db`\n","- **Writes to:** Nothing — this notebook produces analysis, not artifacts\n","- **Consumed by:** The written report and the presentation\n","\n","This stage delivers six analytical queries that demonstrate the pipeline’s value. They are written in SQL against the star schema and answer concrete questions about the data:\n","- Cohort activity distribution: for each cohort, how much time was spent on each activity? → Shows behavioral differences between HARTH and HAR70+.\n","- Subject-level movement profile: for each subject, aggregate all windows of a given activity into one summary row (mean std, window count, mean adjusted MET). → Creates a per-subject movement fingerprint and tests whether cohort patterns hold across individuals or are driven by outliers.\n","- Walking intensity comparison: average sensor standard deviation during walking windows, HARTH vs HAR70+. → Quantifies the movement signal shift between younger and older adults.\n","- Activity-level intensity distribution: how std values spread within each activity, showing that not all walking, sitting, or cycling look the same. → Supports using std to adjust MET values per window.\n","- Calorie-rate rankings per cohort: ranked activities by cal_per_kg_per_minute, separately for HARTH and HAR70+. → Identifies the most efficient calorie burning activities for each population and supports the app’s recommendation engine.\n","- Fairness check: for each activity shared between cohorts, compare calorie rate at a fixed body weight. → Shows that shared activities have very similar calorie costs across cohorts, meaning differences come more from activity mix and movement patterns than biased estimates.\n","\n","Each query is accompanied by its SQL, a result table or visualization, and\n","a plain-language interpretation of what the result reveals."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":71,"metadata":{"id":"aT-MFms8PTng","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070579086,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":16,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}},"outputId":"aadd50db-532f-4b0c-c429-91ff2eb60760"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Database: /content/drive/MyDrive/Data Processing Project/Data/pipeline.db\n","Fact table rows: 84,355\n"]}],"source":["def get_connection(db_path: Path) -> sqlite3.Connection:\n","    \"\"\"Return a SQLite connection with foreign keys enabled.\"\"\"\n","    conn = sqlite3.connect(db_path)\n","    conn.execute(\"PRAGMA foreign_keys = ON\")\n","    return conn\n","\n","conn = get_connection(DB_PATH)\n","n_windows = conn.execute(\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM fact_activity_window\").fetchone()[0]\n","conn.close()\n","\n","print(f\"Database: {DB_PATH}\")\n","print(f\"Fact table rows: {n_windows:,}\")"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"fM8-60dPQKTz"},"source":["Connects to the SQLite database and verifies the fact table is populated before running queries."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"-aJ-QUreQOp9"},"source":["## Query 1: Cohort activity distribution\n","\n","Question: How did each cohort spend their recorded time? Which activities dominate in HARTH vs HAR70+?"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":72,"metadata":{"id":"JO76qClmQHmf","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070579150,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":62,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}},"outputId":"a5cb95d3-9d2f-4a13-9e1e-e5a3ec388ecc"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["         activity_name  harth_windows  harth_pct  har70_windows  har70_pct\n","               sitting          27648      44.59           4768      21.33\n","               walking          11785      19.01          10779      48.22\n","              standing           7085      11.43           4161      18.61\n","                 lying           4141       6.68           2010       8.99\n","           cycling_sit           3805       6.14              0        NaN\n","               running           2907       4.69              0        NaN\n","             shuffling           2168       3.50            544       2.43\n","             stairs_up            786       1.27             44       0.20\n","           stairs_down            691       1.11             49       0.22\n","         cycling_stand            540       0.87              0        NaN\n","  cycling_sit_inactive            366       0.59              0        NaN\n","cycling_stand_inactive             78       0.13              0        NaN\n"]}],"source":["query_1 = \"\"\"\n","WITH totals AS (\n","    SELECT\n","        source,\n","        COUNT(*) AS total_windows\n","    FROM fact_activity_window\n","    GROUP BY source\n",")\n","\n","SELECT\n","    a.activity_name,\n","\n","    SUM(CASE WHEN f.source = 'HARTH' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS harth_windows,\n","    ROUND(\n","        SUM(CASE WHEN f.source = 'HARTH' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) * 100.0 /\n","        MAX(CASE WHEN t.source = 'HARTH' THEN t.total_windows END),\n","        2\n","    ) AS harth_pct,\n","\n","    SUM(CASE WHEN f.source = 'HAR70+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS har70_windows,\n","    ROUND(\n","        SUM(CASE WHEN f.source = 'HAR70+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) * 100.0 /\n","        MAX(CASE WHEN t.source = 'HAR70+' THEN t.total_windows END),\n","        2\n","    ) AS har70_pct\n","\n","FROM fact_activity_window f\n","JOIN dim_activity a\n","    ON f.activity_id = a.activity_id\n","JOIN totals t\n","    ON f.source = t.source\n","\n","GROUP BY a.activity_name\n","ORDER BY harth_windows + har70_windows DESC\n","\"\"\"\n","\n","conn = get_connection(DB_PATH)\n","q1_result = pd.read_sql(query_1, conn)\n","conn.close()\n","\n","print(q1_result.to_string(index=False))"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":73,"metadata":{"id":"nA-0it_vQTxM","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":555},"executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070579420,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":257,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}},"outputId":"0a212b00-e1ae-42f6-d7a6-d8745f008b30"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 1400x700 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"source":["# use your existing q1_result dataframe\n","df = q1_result.copy()\n","\n","# sort by total percentage for cleaner display\n","df[\"total_pct\"] = df[\"harth_pct\"].fillna(0) + df[\"har70_pct\"].fillna(0)\n","df = df.sort_values(\"total_pct\", ascending=False)\n","\n","# positions\n","x = np.arange(len(df))\n","width = 0.38\n","\n","# plot\n","plt.figure(figsize=(14,7))\n","\n","plt.bar(x - width/2, df[\"harth_pct\"], width, label=\"HARTH (25–68)\")\n","plt.bar(x + width/2, df[\"har70_pct\"], width, label=\"HAR70+ (70–95)\")\n","\n","# labels\n","plt.xticks(x, df[\"activity_name\"], rotation=45, ha=\"right\")\n","plt.ylabel(\"Percentage of Cohort Windows\")\n","plt.xlabel(\"Activity\")\n","plt.title(\"Activity Distribution Comparison by Cohort\")\n","plt.legend()\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","\n","plt.show()"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"7diSzjgv3qzt"},"source":["The results reflect clear age related behavior differences between the two cohorts. HARTH participants (ages 25 to 68) spend the largest share of recorded time sitting (44.6%): at the office, but still show a wider mix of movement such as running, cycling, and stair use. HAR70+ participants (ages 70 to 95) are more concentrated in lower intensity daily movement, with walking making up 48.2% of all windows and standing 18.6%. Higher intensity activities are absent in the older cohort, which is consistent with reduced mobility and different lifestyle patterns at advanced ages. Overall, HARTH shows more activity variety, while HAR70+ is centered around functional movement such as walking and standing."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"pnzyu4URQh8D"},"source":["## Query 2: Subject-level movement profile\n","\n","Question: Does the cohort-level pattern hold for each individual subject, or is it driven by a few outliers?"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":74,"metadata":{"id":"xsuG-mApQWGs","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777070579505,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":89,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}},"outputId":"1cafaa84-477e-4e3f-c87f-6cb90b1b4478"},"outputs"